[[File:Joe_Biden_in_1987_at_White_House.png|thumb]]

1987年6月9日，拜登正式宣布参加1988年民主党党内总统选举。<ref name="nyt-1987-ann">{{Cite news |last=Dionne Jr. |first=E. J. |date=1987-06-10 |title=Biden Joins Campaign for the Presidency |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/06/10/us/biden-joins-campaign-for-the-presidency.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2017-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171105150453/http://www.nytimes.com/1987/06/10/us/biden-joins-campaign-for-the-presidency.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他被认为是一个强有力的候选人，因为他的形象温和、演讲能力不俗，以[[美国参议院司法委员会|参议院司法委员会]]主席的身份在即将举行的{{Link-en|罗伯特·博克最高法院提名听证会|Robert Bork Supreme Court nomination}}頻繁曝光、对[[嬰兒潮|嬰兒潮]]一代富有吸引力。如果拜登当选，他将成为仅次于约翰·肯尼迪之后第二年轻的总统。<ref name="dmn-87" /><ref name="nyt083187">{{Cite news |last=Toner |first=Robin |date=1987-08-31 |title=Biden, Once the Field's Hot Democrat, Is Being Overtaken by Cooler Rivals |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/08/31/us/biden-once-the-field-s-hot-democrat-is-being-overtaken-by-cooler-rivals.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084657/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/08/31/us/biden-once-the-field-s-hot-democrat-is-being-overtaken-by-cooler-rivals.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="See How They Run" />{{rp|83}}他在1987年第一季度筹集的资金比任何其他候选人都多。<ref name="nyt083187" /><ref name="See How They Run" />{{rp|83}}

到了8月，拜登的竞选信息因工作人员的竞争而变得混乱。<ref name="See How They Run" />{{rp|108–109}}9月，他被指责[[抄袭|抄袭]]了[[工党_(英国)|英国工党]]领袖[[尼尔·基诺克|尼尔·基诺克]]的演讲<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dowd |first=Maureen |date=1987-09-12 |title=Biden's Debate Finale: An Echo From Abroad |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/12/us/biden-s-debate-finale-an-echo-from-abroad.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2017-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215003637/http://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/12/us/biden-s-debate-finale-an-echo-from-abroad.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，拜登在讲自己是家里首个上大学的人时有与基诺克所言相似的句子。拜登曾将类似表述归功于基诺克<ref>{{Cite news |last=Randolph |first=Eleanor |date=1987-09-13 |title=Plagiarism Suggestion Angers Biden's Aides |page=A6 |work=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1987/09/13/plagiarism-suggestion-angers-bidens-aides/912bfcf1-b3f3-4850-a14d-e8b0bee1ed63/ |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081200/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1987/09/13/plagiarism-suggestion-angers-bidens-aides/912bfcf1-b3f3-4850-a14d-e8b0bee1ed63/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="lat-speech" />，但他在8月下旬的两个场合却没有这样做<ref name="lat-speech">{{Cite news |last1=Risen |first1=James |last2=Shogan |first2=Robert |date=1987-09-16 |title=Differing Versions Cited on Source of Passages: Biden Facing New Flap Over Speeches |work=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1987-09-16-mn-5412-story.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081219/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1987-09-16-mn-5412-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Whose Broad Stripes">{{Cite book|last1=Germond|first1=Jack|url=https://archive.org/details/whosebroadstripe00germ|title=Whose Broad Stripes and Bright Stars? The Trivial Pursuit of the Presidency 1988|last2=Witcover|first2=Jules|publisher=Warner Books|year=1989|isbn=0-446-51424-1}}</ref>{{rp|230–232}}当年早些时候，拜登还使用了[[罗伯特·肯尼迪|罗伯特·肯尼迪]]1967年演讲中的段落（他的助手承担了责任）和[[约翰·肯尼迪|约翰·肯尼迪]]的就职演说。两年前，他还使用过[[休伯特·汉弗莱|休伯特·汉弗莱]]1976年的一段话。<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dowd |first=Maureen |date=1987-09-16 |title=Biden Is Facing Growing Debate On His Speeches |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/16/us/biden-is-facing-growing-debate-on-his-speeches.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081135/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/16/us/biden-is-facing-growing-debate-on-his-speeches.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登回应说，政治家们经常相互借鉴，他的一个竞争对手[[杰西·杰克逊|杰西·杰克逊]]曾打电话给他，称他（杰克逊）也使用了汉弗莱的材料。<ref name="aap08-bio" /><ref name="nyt091887">{{Cite news |last=Dionne |first=E. J., Jr. |date=1987-09-18 |title=Biden Admits Plagiarism in School But Says It Was Not 'Malevolent' |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE3DB143FF93BA2575AC0A961948260 |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2011-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110120023426/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE3DB143FF93BA2575AC0A961948260 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

几天后，拜登在法学院时的事被媒体曝光，他当时引用了《福特汉姆法律评论》的一篇文章，但却没有提供足够的注释。<ref name="nyt091887" />拜登在事后被要求重修课程，并以高分通过。<ref>{{Cite news |last=May |first=Lee |date=1987-09-18 |title=Biden Admits Plagiarism in Writing Law School Brief |work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]] |url=http://articles.latimes.com/print/1987-09-18/news/mn-5748_1_law-school |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2013-09-11 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130911001224/http://articles.latimes.com/print/1987-09-18/news/mn-5748_1_law-school |dead-url=no }}</ref>应拜登的要求，特拉华州最高法院专业人员责任委员会对该事件进行了审查，并得出结论称拜登没有违反任何规则。<ref name="nyt-cleared">{{Cite news |date=1989-05-29 |title=Professional Board Clears Biden In Two Allegations of Plagiarism |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE1DD1230F93AA15756C0A96F948260 |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2008-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202123351/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE1DD1230F93AA15756C0A96F948260 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登曾经对自己的早年生活做了一些虚假或夸大其词的说法，例如他在大学里获得了三个学位，曾靠全额[[獎學金|獎學金]]上的[[法学院|法学院]]，毕业成绩在班上名列前茅<ref name="nyt092287">{{Cite news |last=Dionne |first=E. J., Jr. |date=1987-09-22 |title=Biden Admits Errors and Criticizes Latest Report |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/22/us/biden-admits-errors-and-criticizes-latest-report.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081243/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/22/us/biden-admits-errors-and-criticizes-latest-report.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2008-08-23 |title=1988 Road to the White House with Sen. Biden |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D1j0FS0Z6ho |access-date=2012-10-03 |publisher=[[C-SPAN|C-SPAN]] via YouTube |archive-date=2008-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081114231347/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D1j0FS0Z6ho |dead-url=no }}</ref>，以及他曾参加过[[民權運動|民權運動]]。<ref>{{Cite news |last=Flegenheimer |first=Matt |date=2019-06-03 |title=Biden's First Run for President Was a Calamity. Some Missteps Still Resonate. |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/03/us/politics/biden-1988-presidential-campaign.html |access-date=2019-06-03 |archive-date=2019-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603140340/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/03/us/politics/biden-1988-presidential-campaign.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>竞选相关的其他媒体报道十分有限，导致拜登早年的这些问题被放大。<ref>{{Cite book |last=Pomper |first=Gerald M. |url=https://archive.org/details/electionof1988re00pomp/page/37 |title=The Election of 1988 |publisher=Chatham House Publishers |year=1989 |isbn=0-934540-77-2 |page=[https://archive.org/details/electionof1988re00pomp/page/37 37] |chapter=The Presidential Nominations |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/electionof1988re00pomp}}</ref>1987年9月23日，拜登退出了选举，他说他的候选人资格已经被他过去的「不實阴影」所占据。<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dionne Jr. |first=E. J. |date=1987-09-24 |title=Biden Withdraws Bid for President in Wake of Furor |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/24/us/biden-withdraws-bid-for-president-in-wake-of-furor.html |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2017-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221235355/http://www.nytimes.com/1987/09/24/us/biden-withdraws-bid-for-president-in-wake-of-furor.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 脑部肿瘤 ===
1988年2月，拜登再次面临人生考验。在数次发作越来越严重的颈部疼痛之后，拜登被救护车送往[[沃尔特·里德国家军事医疗中心|沃尔特·里德国家军事医疗中心]]进行手术，他接受手术切除他的两个脑[[動脈瘤|動脈瘤]]，因为其中有一个已经开始漏出，境况凶险。<ref>{{cite news |accessdate=2008-08-23 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/02/23/science/the-doctors-world-subtle-clues-are-often-the-only-warnings-of-perilous-aneurysms.html |title=The Doctor's World; Subtle Clues Are Often The Only Warnings Of Perilous Aneurysms |author=Altman, Lawrence, M.D. |work=New York Times |date=1988-02-23 |archive-date=2020-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200428023004/https://www.nytimes.com/1988/02/23/science/the-doctors-world-subtle-clues-are-often-the-only-warnings-of-perilous-aneurysms.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nyt-4cmed">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/20/us/politics/20health.html|title=Many Holes in Disclosure of Nominees' Health|last=Altman|first=Lawrence K.|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2008-10-19|accessdate=2008-10-26|archive-date=2010-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100225194337/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/20/us/politics/20health.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在休养期间，他还患上了[[肺栓塞|肺栓塞]]，这是一种严重的[[併發症|併發症]]。在5月第二次动脉瘤手术后，术后护理与康复使得拜登有七个月未能到参议院工作。<ref name="nyt-4cmed" />

=== 参议院司法委员会 ===
[[File:Biden_Crime_Bill.jpg|thumb]]总统签署{{Internal link helper/en|1994年犯罪法案|Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act}}时讲话]]

拜登长期在[[美国参议院司法委员会|美国参议院司法委员会]]任职，他在1987年至1995年担任该委员会主席，从1981年至1987年和1995年至1997年为少数党最资深成员。

拜登以主席的身份主持了两次极具争议性的[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]]大法官提名听证会。<ref name="aap08-bio" />在1988年罗伯特·博克（Robert Bork）被提名时，拜登推翻了他在前一年接受采访时的立場，反對提名博克。他因此激怒了保守派，<ref name="bronner">Bronner, ''Battle for Justice'', pp. 138–139, 214, 305.</ref>但在听证会结束时，拜登因其在听证会期间所展示的公正、幽默和勇气而受到赞扬。<ref name="bronner" /><ref name="nyt-lg-87">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/10/08/us/washington-talk-the-bork-hearings-for-biden-epoch-of-belief-epoch-of-incredulity.html |title=Washington Talk: The Bork Hearings; For Biden: Epoch of Belief, Epoch of Incredulity |last=Greenhouse |first=Linda |newspaper=The New York Times |date=1987-10-08 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2021-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111141909/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/10/08/us/washington-talk-the-bork-hearings-for-biden-epoch-of-belief-epoch-of-incredulity.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登拒绝了一些反对博克的人所持的论点，<ref name="aap08-bio" />他将自己对博克的反对意见定位于博克强烈的[[原教旨主義|原教旨主義]]与美国宪法规定的自由和[[隐私权_(美国)|隐私权]]超出[[宪法|宪法]]文本中明确列举的权利这一观点之间的冲突。博克的提名在司法委员会中以9比5的票数被否决，<ref name="nyt-lg-87" />然后在参议院全体会议上以58比42的票数被否决。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/10/24/us/senate-s-roll-call-on-the-bork-vote.html|title=Senate's Roll-Call On the Bork Vote|date=1987-10-24|newspaper=The New York Times|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084644/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/10/24/us/senate-s-roll-call-on-the-bork-vote.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在1991年[[克拉倫斯·托馬斯|克拉倫斯·托馬斯]]的提名听证会上，拜登就宪法问题提出的问题常常是错综复杂，以至于托马斯有时会跟不上，<ref name="mayer-abramson">Mayer; Abramson, ''Strange Justice'', p. 213, 218, 336.</ref>托马斯后来写道，拜登的问题就像“故意砸向选手的棒球”一样。<ref name="thomas-vi">{{cite news |title=Clarence Thomas: A Silent Justice Speaks Out: Part VI: Becoming a Judge—and perhaps a Justice |last=Greenburg |first=Jan Crawford |publisher=ABC News |date=2007-09-30 |url=http://www.abcnews.go.com/TheLaw/Story?id=3664944&page=4 |accessdate=2008-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622121644/https://abcnews.go.com/TheLaw/Story?id=3664944&page=4 |archive-date=2011-06-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在委员会听证会结束后，公众得知[[奧克拉荷馬大學|奧克拉荷馬大學]]法学院教授安妮塔·希尔（Anita Hill）指控托马斯在他们共事时性骚扰她。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=2101289|title=Nina Totenberg, NPR Biography|accessdate=2008-05-31|publisher=NPR|archive-date=2008-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080414042451/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=2101289|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Excerpt from Nina Totenberg's breaking National Public Radio report on Anita Hill's accusation of sexual harassment by Clarence Thomas.|url=http://jwa.org/feminism/_html/_transcripts/transcript_JWA071a.htm|accessdate=2008-10-05|date=1991-10-06|publisher=NPR|archive-date=2009-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221202700/http://jwa.org/feminism/_html/_transcripts/transcript_JWA071a.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登已经知道了其中一些指控，但最初只与委员会分享，因为希尔当时不愿作证。<ref name="aap08-bio" />委员会听证会因此再次重启，希尔出庭作证，但拜登不允许其他证人作证，如一名提出类似指控的妇女和性骚扰问题专家。<ref name="nyt-hill">{{cite news |url=https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/08/23/biden-and-anita-hill-revisited/ |title=Biden and Anita Hill, Revisited |last=Phillips |first=Kate |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-09-12 |archive-date=2008-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080911204456/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/08/23/biden-and-anita-hill-revisited/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登说，他要维护托马斯的隐私和听证会的体面。<ref name="mayer-abramson" /><ref name="nyt-hill" />最终，参议院全体议员以52比48票确认了托马斯的提名，拜登则反对。<ref name="aap08-bio" />自由派和妇女团体认为拜登对听证会处理不当，觉得他在支持希尔方面做得不够，<ref name="nyt-hill" />拜登后来开始注重寻找愿意在司法委员会上担职的女性成员，并在委员会的立法议程中强调妇女问题，<ref name="aap08-bio" />2019年，他告诉希尔，他对自己在听证会期间对待她的做法感到遗憾，但希尔在事后表示，她仍然不满意。<ref name="NYT-Stolberg-Hulse">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/25/us/politics/joe-biden-anita-hill.html|title=Joe Biden Expresses Regret to Anita Hill, but She Says 'I'm Sorry' Is Not Enough|last1=Stolberg|first1=Sheryl Gay|date=2019-04-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-25|last2=Martin|first2=Jonathan|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2019-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425205328/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/25/us/politics/joe-biden-anita-hill.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登在90年代[[白水事件|白水事件]]和[[莱温斯基丑闻|莱温斯基丑闻]]调查期间对独立检察官肯尼斯·斯塔尔（Kenneth Starr）提出批评，称在另一位独立检察官被授予类似权力之前，“将是地狱里的寒冷日子。”<ref>''Almanac of American Politics'' 2000, p. 372.</ref>在弹劾克林顿总统期间，他投票支持无罪。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/stories/1999/02/12/senate.vote/ |title=How the senators voted on impeachment |work=CNN |date=1999-02-12 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081326/https://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/stories/1999/02/12/senate.vote/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2000年代，拜登发起了信用卡发卡机构寻求的破产立法。<ref name="aap08-bio" />比尔·克林顿总统在2000年否决了该法案，但该法案在2005年作为《{{Internal link helper/en|防止破产滥用和消费者保护法案|Bankruptcy Abuse Prevention and Consumer Protection Act}}》获得通过，<ref name="aap08-bio" />拜登是18名投赞成票的民主党人之一，而绝大多数的民主党人和[[消费者权益|消费者权益]]组织则反对该法案。<ref>{{cite news|last=Pilkington|first=Ed|date=2019-12-02|title=How Biden Helped Create the Student Debt Problem He Now Promises to Fix|newspaper=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/dec/02/joe-biden-student-loan-debt-2005-act-2020|accessdate=2020-03-08|archive-date=2020-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306071514/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/dec/02/joe-biden-student-loan-debt-2005-act-2020|dead-url=no}}</ref>作为参议员，拜登强烈支持增加[[美鐵|美鐵]]的投资和加强铁路安全。<ref name="aap08-366" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Verma|first=Pranshu|date=2020-10-24|title=Biden, an Amtrak Evangelist, Could Be a Lifeline for a Rail Agency in Crisis|language=en-US|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/10/24/us/biden-amtrak-covid.html|access-date=2020-11-19|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119015056/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/10/24/us/biden-amtrak-covid.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 參議院外交委員會 ===
