拜登也是[[美国参议院外交委员会|美国参议院外交委员会]]的长期成员。他于1997年成为该委员会的少数党成员，并在2001年6月至2003年和2007年至2009年担任该委员会主席。<ref name="aap08-365" />他总体上持偏向[[自由主义|自由主义]]的[[国际主义|国际主义]]立场。<ref name="nyt-foreign">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/24/world/americas/24iht-policy.4.15591832.html | title=In Biden, Obama chooses a foreign policy adherent of diplomacy before force | last=Gordon | first=Michael R. | newspaper=The New York Times | date=2008-08-24 | accessdate=2009-11-05 | archive-date=2013-02-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130227192937/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/24/world/americas/24iht-policy.4.15591832.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="lat-foreign" />他和[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]人保持了良好的合作关系，有时还会反对自己党派的某些主张。<ref name="aap08-365" /><ref name="lat-foreign" />在委员会任职期间，拜登会见了至少来自60个国家和国际组织的150名领导人，成为了[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]在[[外交政策|外交政策]]方面的著名声音。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/09/23/meetings_with_foreign_leaders.html |title=Meetings with Foreign Leaders? Biden's Been There, Done That |last=Kessler |first=Glenn |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2008-09-23 |accessdate=2009-11-05 |archive-date=2012-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120112112314/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/09/23/meetings_with_foreign_leaders.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登在1991年投票反对授权发动[[海湾战争|海湾战争]]，<ref name="lat-foreign">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-aug-24-na-foreignpol24-story.html |title=Joe Biden respected—if not always popular—for foreign policy record |last1=Richter |first1=Paul |last2=Levey |first2=Noam N. |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2008-08-24 |accessdate=2009-11-05 |archive-date=2019-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502051910/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-aug-24-na-foreignpol24-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>与55名民主党参议员中的45名观点一致。他指出在反伊拉克联盟中，美国几乎承担了所有的负担。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/01/13/world/confrontation-gulf-congress-acts-authorize-war-gulf-margins-are-5-votes-senate.html |title=Congress Acts to Authorize War in Gulf |last=Clymer |first=Adam |newspaper=The New York Times |date=1991-01-13 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081353/https://www.nytimes.com/1991/01/13/world/confrontation-gulf-congress-acts-authorize-war-gulf-margins-are-5-votes-senate.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1991年，拜登在听闻[[塞尔维亚|塞尔维亚]]在[[克羅埃西亞獨立戰爭|克羅埃西亞獨立戰爭]]期间所犯的暴行后，对[[南斯拉夫內戰|南斯拉夫战争]]产生了浓厚的兴趣。<ref name="nyt-foreign" />[[波士尼亞戰爭|波士尼亞戰爭]]爆发后，拜登成为了最早呼吁解除武器禁运、训练波斯尼亚[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]并派[[北约|北约]]空袭支持、调查战争罪行的“解除与打击”政策的人之一。<ref name="nyt-foreign" /><ref name="aap08-365" />[[乔治·沃克·布什|布什]]和[[比尔·克林顿|克林顿]]政府都不愿意实施这一政策，担心[[巴尔干半岛|巴尔干地区]]的纠葛。<ref name="nyt-foreign" /><ref name="lat-foreign" />1993年4月，拜登在巴尔干地区呆了一周，与塞尔维亚领导人[[斯洛博丹·米洛舍维奇|斯洛博丹·米洛舍维奇]]举行了长达3小时的紧张面谈。<ref name="wapo-bosnia">{{cite news | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/06/AR2008100602681.html | title=Biden Played Less Than Key Role in Bosnia Legislation | last=Kessler | first=Glenn | newspaper=The Washington Post | date=2008-10-07 | accessdate=2009-11-05 | archive-date=2009-08-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826101923/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/06/AR2008100602681.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登对他说：“我认为你就是一个该死的战犯，你应该被当作战犯来审判。”<ref name="wapo-bosnia" />

拜登在1992年提出了一个修正案，迫使布什政府武装波斯尼亚人，但他在1994年软化了自己的立场，因为克林顿政府在第二年签署由[[鲍勃·多尔|鲍勃·多尔]]和[[喬·李伯曼|喬·李伯曼]]所提出的一项更强有力的措施前倾向于采取更加平和的立场。<ref name="wapo-bosnia" />这一举动导致了北约[[维和行动|维和行动]]的成功。<ref name="nyt-foreign" />拜登称他在90年代中期在影响巴尔干政策中扮演的角色，是他在外交政策相關事宜上「最為自豪的一刻」。<ref name="lat-foreign" />

在[[科索沃战争|科索沃战争]]期间，拜登支持1999年[[北约轰炸南斯拉夫|北约轰炸南斯拉夫]]共和国的行動。<ref name="nyt-foreign" />他与[[約翰·麥凱恩|約翰·麥凱恩]]共同提出了麦凯恩·拜登科索沃决议案，呼吁克林顿总统动用一切必要的武力，包括地面部队，就南斯拉夫对科索沃[[阿爾巴尼亞族|阿爾巴尼亞族]]人的行动与米洛舍维奇对抗。<ref name="lat-foreign" /><ref name="wsj082508">{{cite news | url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB121954185485266719 | title=Biden, McCain Have a Friendship—and More—in Common | last=Holmes | first=Elizabeth | newspaper=The Wall Street Journal | date=2008-08-25 | accessdate=2009-11-05 | archive-date=2015-10-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194520/http://www.wsj.com/articles/SB121954185485266719 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登是2001年[[阿富汗戰爭_(2001年)|阿富汗戰爭]]的坚定支持者，他说：“无论付出什么代价，我们都应该这样做。”<ref name=TNR.hawk>{{cite magazine|last1=Crowley|first1=Michael|title=HawkDown|url=https://newrepublic.com/article/politics/hawk-down|magazine=The New Republic|quote=原文：“Even before Obama announced his run for president, Biden was warning that Afghanistan, not Iraq, was the 'central front' in the war against Al Qaeda, requiring a major U.S. commitment. 'Whatever it takes, we should do it,' Biden said in February 2002.”|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194518/http://www.newrepublic.com/article/politics/hawk-down|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登以参议院外交关系委员会负责人的身份在2002年说，[[萨达姆·侯赛因|萨达姆·侯赛因]]是对国家安全的威胁，除了“消除”这一威胁，美国别无选择。<ref name="MTP04292007">{{cite news |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/18381961 |work=Meet the Press |title=MTP Transcript for April 29, 2007 |first=Tim |last=Russert |publisher=NBC News |date=2007-04-29 |page=2 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2020-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208191954/https://www.nbcnews.com/id/18381961 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2002年10月，他对《{{Internal link helper/en|对伊拉克使用武力授权书|Authorization for Use of Military Force Against Iraq Resolution of 2002}}》投了赞成票，批准美国[[伊拉克战争|入侵伊拉克]]。<ref name="lat-foreign" />拜登以委员会主席的身份召集了一系列证人为授权书作证。他们的证词严重歪曲了萨达姆及其世俗政府的意图、历史和地位，而萨达姆及其世俗政府是[[基地组织|基地组织]]的公然敌人，他们还吹捧虚构的伊拉克[[大规模杀伤性武器|大规模杀伤性武器]]。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Joe Biden championed the Iraq war. Will that come back to haunt him now? {{!}} Mark Weisbrot|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/feb/17/joe-biden-role-iraq-war|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2020-02-18|accessdate=2020-12-20|issn=0261-3077|language=en-GB|first=Mark|last=Weisbrot|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109174540/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/feb/17/joe-biden-role-iraq-war|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登最终成为战争的批评者，并将自己曾经的投票支持和在过程中的作用视为“错误”，但他也没有推动美国撤军。<ref name="lat-foreign" /><ref name="wapo-bosnia" />他支持拨款支付占领费，但一再主张战争应该国际化，需要更多的士兵，而布什政府应该在冲突的成本和时间长短上“与美国人民意愿持平」。<ref name="aap08-365">''Almanac of American Politics'' 2008, p. 365.</ref><ref name="wsj082508" />

到2006年底，拜登的立场发生了很大转变，他反对在2007年增兵，<ref name="lat-foreign" /><ref name="wapo-bosnia" />称[[戴维·彼得雷乌斯|戴维·彼得雷乌斯]]将军认为增兵能够奏效是“没用，完全错误”。<ref name="nytm-traub" />拜登转而主张将伊拉克划分为一个由三个民族国家组成的松散联邦<ref name="Divided">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/weekinreview/19shanker.html |title=Divided They Stand, but on Graves |first=Thom |last=Shanker |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2007-08-19 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081421/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/weekinreview/19shanker.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2006年11月，拜登和外交关系委员会名誉主席莱斯利·盖尔布（Leslie Gelb）一起发布了一项结束伊拉克教派暴力的全面战略。<ref name="LAT20071001">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2007-oct-01-fg-iraq1-story.html |first1=Ned |last1=Parker |first2=Raheem |last2=Salman |title=U.S. vote unites Iraqis in anger |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2007-10-01 |accessdate=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081500/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2007-oct-01-fg-iraq1-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>该计划没有延续目前的做法或撤军，而是呼吁“第三条道路”：将伊拉克联邦化，让[[库尔德人|库尔德人]]、[[什叶派|什叶派]]和[[遜尼派|遜尼派]]在自己的地区有“喘息空间”。<ref name="witcover" />{{rp|572–573}}2007年9月，参议院通过了一项不具约束力的决议，支持该计划。<ref name="LAT20071001" />但人们对该计划并不熟悉，政治上也没有支持者，导致起最终未能获得支持。<ref name="nytm-traub" />伊拉克政治领导层谴责该决议是事实上的国家分治，而[[美國駐巴格達大使館|美國駐巴格達大使館]]则发表了一份声明与之保持距离。<ref name="LAT20071001" />2008年5月，他对美国总统[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·布什]]在[[以色列|以色列]]议会的一次演讲提出尖锐批评，他在演讲中把一些民主党人比作二战前姑息[[阿道夫·希特勒|希特勒]]的西方领导人。拜登称他的演讲是“胡说八道”、“恶语相向”、“令人愤怒”，但他后来为自己的语言道歉。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/05/15/bush.dems/index.html |title=Dems fire back at Bush on 'appeasement' statement |last=Henry |first=Ed |work=CNN |date=2008-05-16 |accessdate=2008-09-02 |archive-date=2008-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080920093550/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/05/15/bush.dems/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 参议员生涯评价 ===
[[File:Joe_Biden,_official_photo_portrait_2.jpg|thumb]]

拜登于1972年当选参议员，并非常顺利地赢得了之后的连任选举。1974年，剛上任参议员不久的拜登就被当时的[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]评为“200个未来有所作为的新面孔”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,879402-6,00.html|title=200 Faces for the Future|publisher=TIME|date=1974-07-15|accessdate=2008-08-23|archive-date=2013-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813045404/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,879402-6,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后相继于1978年战胜詹姆斯·巴克斯特，1984年战胜约翰·巴瑞斯，1990年战胜简·布雷迪，1996年和2002年两次胜过雷蒙德·克莱特沃斯，并且其支持率通常高于60%。<ref name="aap08-366" />1981年，拜登获得了[[聖約瑟夫大學|聖約瑟夫大學]]的[[荣誉学位|荣誉学位]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sju.edu/ir/documents/HonDegreeRecip_IR2008.pdf |title=Saint Joseph's University Honorary Degrees |accessdate=2008-08-31 |archive-date=2008-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080904003527/http://www.sju.edu/ir/documents/HonDegreeRecip_IR2008.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>他是特拉华州1970年首次当选的威廉·罗斯（William Roth）后的新任参议员，直到2000年罗斯被击败。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/08/23/biden.democrat.vp.candidate/ |title=Obama introduces Biden as running mate |work=CNN |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-09-18 |archive-date=2015-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150109172417/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/08/23/biden.democrat.vp.candidate/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>截至2020年，他是美国历史上任期第18长的参议员。<ref name="26 Aug 2018">{{cite web|title=Longest Serving Senators|url=https://www.senate.gov/senators/longest_serving_senators.htm|website=United States Senate|publisher=United States Senate|accessdate=2018-08-26|archive-date=2018-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919101452/https://www.senate.gov/senators/longest_serving_senators.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登一直被列为参议院最不富裕的议员之一，<ref name="lat082408nw">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-aug-24-na-assess24-story.html |title=Demographics part of calculation: Biden adds experience, yes, but he could also help with Catholics, blue-collar whites and women |last=Wallsten |first=Peter |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2008-08-24 |accessdate=2008-08-25 |archive-date=2019-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515025410/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-aug-24-na-assess24-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/news/education/higher/articles/2008/08/24/a_look_at_bidens_net_worth/ |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |newspaper=The Boston Globe |title=A look at Biden's net worth |date=2008-08-24 |accessdate=2009-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120725145844/http://www.boston.com/news/education/higher/articles/2008/08/24/a_look_at_bidens_net_worth/ |archive-date=2012-07-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/13/us/politics/13biden.html |title=Biden Releases Tax Returns, in Part to Pressure Rivals |last=Broder |first=John M. |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2008-09-13 |accessdate=2008-09-13 |archive-date=2011-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110425024153/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/13/us/politics/13biden.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他认为这是因为他年轻时就当选的缘故，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2008/09/12/biden-tax-returns-revealed/ |title=Biden tax returns revealed |last=Mooney |first=Alexander |work=CNN |date=2008-09-12 |accessdate=2008-09-13 |archive-date=2008-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913001912/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2008/09/12/biden-tax-returns-revealed/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>他觉得不太富裕的公职人员可能会受到诱惑，从而接受他人捐款以换取政治利益，因此在第一个任期内就提出了竞选财务改革措施。<ref name="cby-44" />

政治作家霍华德·芬曼（Howard Fineman）曾写道：“拜登不是一个学者，他也不是一个理论思想家，但他是一个伟大的街头政治家。他是来自于[[斯克蘭頓_(賓夕法尼亞州)|斯克兰顿]]的一长串劳动人民中——汽车销售员、汽车经销商，知道如何做销售的人。他有那种伟大的[[愛爾蘭裔美國人|愛爾蘭]]天赋。”<ref name="watn020109" />政治专栏作家大卫·布罗德（David S. Broder）认为，拜登随着时间的推移而成长：“他对真实的人作出回应——这是始终如一的。而且他理解自己和与其他政治家打交道的能力也变得更好了。”<ref name="watn020109" />记者詹姆斯·特拉布（James Traub）曾评价称：“拜登是那种内在快乐的人，他对别人可以像对自己一样慷慨。”<ref name="nytm-traub" />2006年，特拉华州报纸专栏作家哈里·西马尔（Harry Themal）写道，拜登“占据了民主党的理智中心。”<ref name="themal">{{cite news | title=Biden says he's on track for 2008 run | last=Themal|first=Harry F. | work=The News Journal | date=2006-01-23}}</ref>

拜登以好辩著称，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0601/12/sitroom.01.html |title=Transcripts |work=The Situation Room |publisher=CNN |date=2006-01-12 |accessdate=2008-09-21 |archive-date=2008-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080719103425/http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0601/12/sitroom.01.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他是一个强有力的演讲者和辩论者，<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Breaking News, Analysis, Politics, Blogs, News Photos, Video, Tech Reviews|url=http://content.time.com/time/politics/article/0,8599,1846632,00.html|last=Halperin|first=Mark|date=2008-10-02|journal=Time|language=en-US|issn=0040-781X|access-date=2020-12-27|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103085607/http://content.time.com/time/politics/article/0,8599,1846632,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>也是一位周日早上[[脱口秀_(歐美)|脱口秀]]节目的理想嘉宾。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Stephen Colbert’s interview with Joe Biden is the best he's ever done|url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/9/11/9310497/stephen-colbert-joe-biden-late-show-interview|accessdate=2020-12-27|date=2015-09-11|last=Welch|first=Chris|work=The Verge|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081530/https://www.theverge.com/2015/9/11/9310497/stephen-colbert-joe-biden-late-show-interview|dead-url=no}}</ref>他常常会偏离预先准备好的草稿，<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/ben-smith/2008/12/biden-enemy-of-the-prepared-remarks-014500 |title=Biden, enemy of the prepared remarks |last=Smith |first=Ben |work=Politico |date=2008-12-02 |accessdate=2008-12-02 |archive-date=2015-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911131530/http://www.politico.com/blogs/ben-smith/2008/12/biden-enemy-of-the-prepared-remarks-014500 |dead-url=no }}</ref>有时也会不小心“把脚放在嘴里”（指犯错误）。<ref name="abc-loq">{{cite news | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Story?id=2838420 | title=A Biden Problem: Foot in Mouth | last=Tapper | first=Jake | publisher=ABC News | date=2007-01-31 | accessdate=2008-09-21 | archive-date=2008-08-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080827211803/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Story?id=2838420 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nyt-no2">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/20/us/politics/20biden.html |title=Meanwhile, the Other No. 2 Keeps On Punching |last=Leibovich |first=Mark |work=The New York Times |date=2008-09-19 |accessdate=2008-09-20 |archive-date=2013-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130227193018/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/20/us/politics/20biden.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1998/03/19/world/senate-struggles-to-pay-attention-to-the-remapping-of-nato.html |title=Senate Struggles to Pay Attention to the Remapping of NATO |last=Seelye |first=Katharine Q. |newspaper=The New York Times |date=1998-03-19 |accessdate=2008-09-21 |archive-date=2012-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110045839/http://www.nytimes.com/1998/03/19/world/senate-struggles-to-pay-attention-to-the-remapping-of-nato.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="time-pcs">{{cite news |url=http://content.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1835480,00.html |title=Halperin on Biden: Pros and Cons |last=Halperin |first=Mark |magazine=Time |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-09-21 |archive-date=2014-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140722092813/http://content.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1835480,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》写道，拜登脑子里“薄弱的过滤器使他能够说出几乎任何东西。”<ref name="nyt-no2" />

== 2008年总统选举 ==
=== 个人的总统竞选 ===
{{Main|{{Internal link helper/en|乔·拜登2008年总统竞选活动|Joe Biden 2008 presidential campaign}}}}
[[File:Sen._Joe_Biden_attends_a_Creston_house_party.jpg|thumb]][[克雷斯顿_(爱荷华州)|克雷斯顿]]举行的家庭聚会上竞选]]
拜登在1992年选择不参加总统竞选，部分原因是他曾投票反对授权[[海湾战争|海湾战争]]。<ref name="aap08-366">''Almanac of American Politics'' 2008, p. 366.</ref>2004年拜登也没有参加竞选，因为他觉得自己胜算不大，留在参议院最能为国家服务。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2003/ALLPOLITICS/08/11/biden/index.html |title=Sen. Biden not running for president |work=CNN |date=2003-08-12 |accessdate=2008-09-18 |archive-date=2019-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209123957/http://edition.cnn.com/2003/ALLPOLITICS/08/11/biden/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2007年1月，拜登宣布参加2008年大选。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/01/31/AR2007013100404.html|title=Biden Stumbles at the Starting Gate|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=2008-08-23|date=2007-01-01|last=Balz|first=Dan|archive-date=2017-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018123657/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/01/31/AR2007013100404.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在竞选期间，拜登重点介绍了[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]、他作为参议院主要委员会主席的历史以及他的外交政策经验。拜登否决了他可能成为[[美国国务卿|国务卿]]的猜测，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.observer.com/2007/candidate-secretary-state|title=A Candidate For Secretary Of State|newspaper=The New York Observer|date=2007-06-12|accessdate=2008-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080919053641/http://www.observer.com/2007/candidate-secretary-state|archive-date=2008-09-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>称他只关注总统职位。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=ReMqAAAAIBAJ&pg=6332,4673219 |newspaper=Milwaukee Journal Sentinel |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |title=Biden says he wouldn't be secretary of state|date = 2007-11-30 |page=12A}}</ref>2007年年中，拜登在与[[贝拉克·奥巴马|奥巴马]]相比时强调自己的外交政策专长，他在谈到后者时说：“我认为他可以做好准备，但我不相信他现在准备好了。总统职位可不是适合在职培训的东西。”<ref>{{cite news |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Decision2008/Story?id=3498294&page=1 |title=Transcript: The Democratic Debate |publisher=ABC News |date=2007-08-19 |accessdate=2008-09-24 |archive-date=2008-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011185127/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Decision2008/story?id=3498294&page=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登还说，奥巴马抄袭了他的一些外交政策理念。<ref name="nytm-traub">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/11/29/magazine/29Biden-t.html | title=After Cheney | last=Traub | first=James | magazine=The New York Times Magazine | date=2009-11-24 | page=MM34 | accessdate=2020-12-20 | archive-date=2021-01-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084703/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/11/29/magazine/29Biden-t.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登在竞选期间以单刀直入著称；在一次辩论中，他对共和党候选人[[魯迪·朱利安尼|魯迪·朱利安尼]]说：“他只会在句子里提到三个东西：一个名词，一个动词，和[[九一一袭击事件|九一一]]”（朱利安尼是袭击时的纽约市长）。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.concordmonitor.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20071101/NEWS01/711010358/1043/NEWS01|newspaper=Concord Monitor|title=A noun, a verb and 9/11|last=Farrell|first=Joelle|accessdate=2008-08-23|date=2007-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828010554/http://www.concordmonitor.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20071101%2FNEWS01%2F711010358%2F1043%2FNEWS01|archive-date=2008-08-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>总的来说，拜登的辩论表现有效地混合了幽默和犀利而又出人意料的正经评论。<ref name="gamechange">{{Cite book | first1=John | last1=Heilemann | first2=Mark | last2=Halperin | title=Game Change: Obama and the Clintons, McCain and Palin, and the Race of a Lifetime | url=https://archive.org/details/gamechange00john | publisher=HarperCollins |location=New York | year= 2010 | isbn=978-0-06-173363-5}}</ref>{{rp|336}}

拜登在筹集资金上遇到了困难，也难以吸引民众参加他的集会，在面对奥巴马和参议员[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]的高调参选时，也未能获得吸引力。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nationaljournal.com/conventions/co_20080825_3122.php |title=Conventions 2008: Sen. Joseph Biden (D) |work=National Journal |date=2008-08-25 |accessdate=2008-09-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080906210353/http://www.nationaljournal.com/conventions/co_20080825_3122.php |archive-date=2008-09-06 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在民主党候选人的全国性民调中，他的排名从未超过个位数。在2008年1月3日的第一场比赛中，拜登在[[艾奥瓦州|艾奥瓦州]]党团选举中名列第五，获得略低于1%的州代表名额。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.iowacaucusresults.com/ | title=Iowa Democratic Party Caucus Results | publisher=Iowa Democratic Party | accessdate=2008-08-29 | archive-date=2016-04-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415000251/http://www.iowacaucusresults.com/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>他在当晚退出了竞选。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/01/04/AR2008010400260.html |title=Biden, Dodd Withdraw From Race |last=Murray |first=Shailagh |work=The Washington Post |date=2008-01-04 |accessdate=2008-08-29 |archive-date=2008-05-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080520022844/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/01/04/AR2008010400260.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

尽管没有取得成功，但拜登2008年的竞选活动提高了他在政界的地位，<ref name="gamechange" />{{rp|336}}特别是改变了拜登和奥巴马之间的关系。虽然他们曾一起在参议院外交关系委员会任职，但关系并不密切。拜登曾憎恨奥巴马迅速崛起的政治名声，<ref name="nytm-traub" /><ref name="wolffe-218">Wolffe, ''Renegade'', p. 218.</ref>而奥巴马则曾认为拜登矫揉造作、居高临下。<ref name="gamechange" />{{rp|28, 337–338}}在2007年竞选期间相互了解后，奥巴马欣赏拜登的竞选风格和对工人阶级选民的吸引力，拜登则说他开始相信奥巴马是“货真价实的”。<ref name="wolffe-218" /><ref name="gamechange" />{{rp|28, 337–338}}

=== 携手奥巴马 ===
{{Main|2008年美國總統選舉|巴拉克·奧巴馬2008年美國總統競選活動}}
[[File:Obamas_and_Bidens.jpg|thumb]]

在拜登退出总统竞选后不久，[[贝拉克·奥巴马|奥巴马]]就在私底下告诉他称有兴趣为拜登在其政府里找一个重要的位置。<ref name="ny-lizza">{{cite news |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2008/10/20/bidens-brief |title=Biden's Brief |last=Lizza |first=Ryan |work=The New Yorker |date=2008-10-20 |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-date=2014-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725212805/http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2008/10/20/bidens-brief |dead-url=no }}</ref>当奥巴马向拜登第一次提出担任副总统的可能性时，他拒绝了请求。拜登最初担心副总统职位与参议员一职相比代表着他在地位和话语权上的损失，但他后来改变了主意。<ref name="nytm-traub" /><ref name="pol091609">{{cite news|last=Cummings|first=Jeanne|date=2009-09-16|title=Joe Biden, 'the skunk at the family picnic'|publisher=The Politico|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2009/09/the-skunk-at-the-family-picnic-027211|accessdate=2009-09-17|archive-date=2015-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927053814/http://www.politico.com/story/2009/09/the-skunk-at-the-family-picnic-027211|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2008年6月22日，拜登在NBC節目《[[與媒體見面|與媒體見面]]》中表示，虽然他并不积极寻求副总统提名，但如果得到提名，他将接受。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2008/06/23/biden-id-say-yes-to-being-vp/ |first=Alexander |last=Mooney |title=Biden: I'd say yes to being VP |work=CNN |accessdate=2008-08-23 |date=2008-06-23 |archive-date=2008-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080926083506/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2008/06/23/biden-id-say-yes-to-being-vp/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>8月初，奥巴马和拜登会面讨论了副总统提名的可能性，<ref name="ny-lizza" />两人建立了深厚的个人关系。<ref name="wolffe-218" />2008年8月22日，奥巴马宣布拜登将成为他的竞选伙伴。<ref>{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |title=Obama's veep message to supporters |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/08/23/AR2008082300455.html |first=Jose Antonio |last=Vargas |work=The Washington Post |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-08-23 |archive-date=2010-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101204011137/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/08/23/AR2008082300455.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道称，选择拜登反映了奥巴马希望有一位有[[外交政策|外交政策]]和[[國家安全|國家安全]]经验的人充实票面，而不是为了帮助他赢得一个[[搖擺州|搖擺州]]或者强调他的“变革”（Change）信息。<ref>{{cite news |first1=Adam |last1=Nagourney |first2=Jeff |last2=Zeleny |title=Obama Chooses Biden as Running Mate |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/24/us/politics/24biden.html |work=The New York Times |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-08-23 |archive-date=2009-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090401222653/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/24/us/politics/24biden.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>其他人则指出拜登对[[中產階級|中產階級]]和[[藍領|藍領]]选民的吸引力，以及他愿意积极挑战共和党提名人[[約翰·麥凱恩|約翰·麥凱恩]]的意愿，而奥巴马有时则似乎对挑战麦凯恩的做法感到不舒服。<ref>{{cite news |first=E.J. |last=Dionne |title=Tramps Like Us: How Joe Biden will reassure working class voters and change the tenor of this week's convention |url=https://newrepublic.com/article/62212/tramps-us |work=The New Republic |date=2008-08-25 |accessdate=2008-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828210626/http://tnr.com/politics/story.html?id=2ecbd0b9-c2c4-44d7-824a-603b4a418c74 |archive-date=2008-08-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Wolffe, ''Renegade'', p. 217.</ref>在接受奥巴马的邀请时，拜登排除了在2016年再次竞选总统的可能性，<ref name="ny-lizza" />但他在后来的言论似乎又打消了这一念头，因为他不想因显得对升迁不感兴趣而削弱自己的政治能量。<ref>{{cite news|url= http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2009/06/vp-biden-keeping-the-door-open-for-2016-.html|title= VP Biden Keeping the Door Open for 2016?|last= Travers|first= Karen|date= 2009-06-25|work= Political Punch|publisher= ABC News|accessdate= 2010-10-14|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101017172435/http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2009/06/vp-biden-keeping-the-door-open-for-2016-.html|archive-date= 2010-10-17|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2011/10/21/biden-in-2016/ |title=Biden in 2016? |work=CNN |date=2011-10-21 |accessdate=2011-10-29 |archive-date=2011-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025222449/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2011/10/21/biden-in-2016/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nyt0508122">{{cite news|last=Leibovich|first=Mark|date=2012-05-08|title=For a Blunt Biden, an Uneasy Supporting Role|page=1|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/08/us/politics/for-a-blunt-biden-an-uneasy-supporting-role.html|accessdate=2020-12-24|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081748/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/08/us/politics/for-a-blunt-biden-an-uneasy-supporting-role.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登于8月27日在丹佛举行的2008年[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]全国代表大会上以声音投票的方式正式被提名为民主党副总统候选人。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://newsblaze.com/usnews/politics/democrats-formally-nominate-barack-obama-for-u-s-presidency_60148/ |title=Democrats Formally Nominate Barack Obama for U.S. Presidency |first=Alan |last=Gray |publisher=NewsBlaze |date=2008-08-29 |accessdate=2020-12-24 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081753/https://newsblaze.com/usnews/politics/democrats-formally-nominate-barack-obama-for-u-s-presidency_60148/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登的副总统竞选活动几乎没有获得媒体的关注，因为媒体将其注意力聚焦在了共和党竞选搭档，[[阿拉斯加州|阿拉斯加]]州长[[莎拉·佩林|莎拉·佩林]]身上。<ref name="nyt-no2" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2008/09/joe-who.html |title=Joe Who? |last=Tapper |first=Jake |publisher=ABC News |date=2008-09-14 |accessdate=2008-09-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080915055913/http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2008/09/joe-who.html |archive-date=2008-09-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[皮尤研究中心|皮尤研究中心]]的卓越新闻项目发现，在2008年9月的一个星期里，拜登仅被列入5%的竞选报道中，远低于票上其他三位候选人的报道。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.journalism.org/2008/09/15/pej-campaign-coverage-index-september-8-14-2008/ |title=Northern Exposure Still Dominates the News |publisher=[[Pew_Research_Center|Pew Research Center]] |last=Jurkowitz |first=Mark |date=2008-09-14 |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-date=2013-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109013634/http://www.journalism.org/2008/09/15/pej-campaign-coverage-index-september-8-14-2008/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>不过，拜登还是专注于在[[搖擺州|搖擺州]]的经济困难地区开展竞选活动，并试图赢得蓝领民主党人的支持，尤其是那些曾支持[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]的人。<ref name="nytm-traub" /><ref name="nyt-no2" />尽管拜登与麦凯恩有着长期的私人友谊，但他还是对麦凯恩进行了猛烈的抨击。{{refn|group=注| 拜登在政治上和个人上都很欣赏麦凯恩。2004年5月，他曾敦促麦凯恩与民主党总统候选人[[約翰·福布斯·凱瑞|約翰·福布斯·凱瑞]]一起竞选副总统，称跨党派的选票将有助于弥合美国政治中的“恶性裂痕”。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/id/4961694 |title=McCain Urged to Join Kerry Ticket |agency=[[Reuters|Reuters]] |publisher=[[NBC_News|NBC News]] |date=2004-05-16 |accessdate=2020-12-24 |archive-date=2020-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219053301/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/4961694 |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}拜登说：“那个我曾经认识的家伙已经走了。这真的让我很伤心。”<ref name="nyt-no2" />随着[[2007年–2008年環球金融危機|2008年9月流动性危机]]的爆发，2007-2010年的[[金融危机|金融危机]]达到顶峰，对美国金融体系的救助提议成为了竞选的主要议题，拜登对2008年7000亿美元的《[[經濟穩定緊急法案|經濟穩定緊急法案]]》投了赞成票，该法案后来在参议院以74-25获得通过。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/features/86538/senate-passes-economic-rescue-package/Default.aspx |title=Senate Passes Economic Rescue Package |publisher=NY1 |date=2008-10-01 |accessdate=2008-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005022401/http://www.ny1.com/content/features/86538/senate-passes-economic-rescue-package/Default.aspx |archive-date=2008-10-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

2008年10月2日，拜登在[[圣路易斯_(密苏里州)|圣路易斯]]的[[圣路易斯华盛顿大学|华盛顿大学]]与佩林进行了副总统辩论。辩论后的[[民調|民調]]结果显示，虽然佩林超出了许多选民的预期，但拜登总体上赢得了辩论。<ref name="witcover" />{{rp|655–661}}在竞选活动的最后几天时，拜登把重点放在人口较少、年龄较大、经济条件较差的战场州，特别是[[佛罗里达州|佛罗里达州]]、[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]和[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]，民调显示他在这些地方很受欢迎，而奥巴马则在民主党初选中的竞选活动和表现都不太理想。<ref name="nyt103008">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/31/us/politics/31biden.html |title=Hitting the Backroads, and Having Less to Say |last=Broder |first=John M. |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2008-10-30 |accessdate=2008-10-31 |archive-date=2013-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130227193045/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/31/us/politics/31biden.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="time102908" /><ref name="pol110308">{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2008/11/where-have-you-gone-joe-biden-015205 |title=Where have you gone, Joe Biden? |last=McGrane |first=Victoria |newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2008-11-03 |accessdate=2008-11-03 |archive-date=2015-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194519/http://www.politico.com/story/2008/11/where-have-you-gone-joe-biden-015205 |dead-url=no }}</ref>他还在一些通常投给共和党的州和[[天主教|天主教徒]]居多的地区开展竞选活动。<ref name="pol110308" />

在竞选团队的指示下，拜登的演讲言简意赅，尽量避免不经意的言论，比如关于奥巴马上任后不久就可能会被外国势力挑战的言论就曾引起负面关注。<ref name="nyt103008" /><ref name="time102908">{{cite news |url=https://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1855355,00.html |title=Hidin' Biden: Reining In a Voluble No. 2 |last=Tumulty |first=Karen |magazine=Time |date=2008-10-29 |accessdate=2008-11-01 |archive-date=2014-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109102805/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1855355,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>私下里，拜登的言论曾让奥巴马感到沮丧。他问道：“拜登还要说多少次蠢话？”<ref name="gamechange" />{{rp|411–414, 419}}奥巴马竞选工作人员将拜登的失误称为“-{zh-hans:乔;zh-tw:喬;zh-hk:祖}-弹”，并故意避免让拜登参与竞选策略讨论，这反过来又让拜登感到恼火。<ref name="nyt0508122" />两场竞选活动之间的紧张关系持续了约一个月，直到拜登在给奥巴马的电话中道歉，两人则建立了更牢固的伙伴关系。<ref name="gamechange" />{{rp|411–414}}奥巴马竞选团队策略师大卫·阿克塞尔罗德（David Axelrod）在公开场合说，拜登的高人气评价已经胜过了他任何意料之外的言论。<ref>{{cite news |title=Biden reliable running mate despite gaffes |url=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/144631311/ |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |newspaper=Asbury Park Press |date=2008-10-26 |accessdate=2020-12-24 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084723/https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/144631311/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登在[[皮尤研究中心|皮尤研究中心]]的全国范围民调中获得了60%的支持率，而佩林只获得了44%。<ref name="nyt103008" />

2008年11月4日，奥巴马和拜登以53%的普选票和365张[[选举人票|选举人票]]当选，而麦凯恩-佩林组合只获得了173张选举人票。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/11/04/election.president/index.html |title=Barack Obama wins presidential election |work=CNN |accessdate=2008-11-05 |date=2008-11-04 |archive-date=2008-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081107223835/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/11/04/election.president/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Franke-Ruta |first=Garance |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/the-trail/2008/11/19/mccain_takes_missouri.html |title=McCain Takes Missouri |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2008-11-19 |accessdate=2008-11-19 |archive-date=2012-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120112043539/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/the-trail/2008/11/19/mccain_takes_missouri.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/ELECTION/2008/results/president/ |title=President—Election Center 2008 |work=CNN |accessdate=2008-11-19 |archive-date=2008-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081109050840/http://edition.cnn.com/ELECTION/2008/results/president/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登先前已登记竞选连任[[參議員|參議員]]，后又被奥巴马选为[[副总统|副总统]]候选人。<ref name="ap082408">{{cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/wires/2008Aug24/0,4670,CVNBidenTwoCampaigns,00.html |title=Biden Wages 2 Campaigns At Once |agency=Associated Press |date=2008-08-24 |accessdate=2008-08-29 |first=Randall |last=Chase |publisher=Fox News |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185451/https://www.foxnews.com/wires/2008Aug24/0,4670,CVNBidenTwoCampaigns,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>虽然他同时参与了两场选举，但这是[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]法律所允许的。<ref name="aap08-366">''Almanac of American Politics'' 2008, p. 366.</ref>11月4日，拜登还击败了共和党人克里斯蒂娜·奥唐奈尔（Christine O'Donnell）并成功连任参议员。<ref name="ap110408">{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/politics/2008-11-04-420465768_x.htm |title=Biden wins 7th Senate term but may not serve |last=Nuckols |first=Ben |agency=Associated Press |newspaper=USA Today |date=2008-11-04 |accessdate=2009-02-06 |archive-date=2009-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090226050628/http://www.usatoday.com/news/politics/2008-11-04-420465768_x.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>由于联邦法律禁止任何人同时担任行政官员与国会议员，拜登必须辞去参议员一职才能就任副总统。在赢得这两场竞选后，拜登特意暂缓辞去参议员职务，以便能在2009年1月6日宣誓就任第七个任期。<ref name="dnj010709">{{cite news |url=http://www.delawareonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=2009901070333 |title=A bittersweet oath for Biden |last=Gaudiano |first=Nicole |work=The News Journal |date=2009-01-07 |accessdate=2009-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090212100305/http://www.delawareonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=2009901070333 |archive-date=2009-02-12 |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登成为了有史以来最年轻的开始第七个完整任期的参议员，他说：“我的一生中所赋予的最大荣誉就是作为特拉华州人民的参议员，为他们服务。”<ref name="dnj010709" />拜登在1月15日投下了在参议院的最后一票，支持发放第二笔3500亿美元的《问题资产救助计划》，<ref>{{cite news |first=Trish |last=Turner |agency=Associated Press |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/senate-releases-350-billion-in-bailout-funds-to-obama |title=Senate Releases $350 Billion in Bailout Funds to Obama |work=Fox News |date=2009-01-15 |accessdate=2009-01-25 |archive-date=2019-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230182202/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/senate-releases-350-billion-in-bailout-funds-to-obama |dead-url=no }}</ref>并在当天晚些时候辞去了参议员一职。{{refn|group=注| 经州长任命，拜登的助手[[泰德·考夫曼|泰德·考夫曼]]接替了拜登留下的参议员职位。<ref name="bloom112408" />考夫曼称只会任职两年，直到举行特别选举。<ref name="bloom112408">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=20601087&sid=apZPaTS_UmpM |title=Kaufman Picked by Governor to Fill Biden Senate Seat (Update 3) |last=Milford |first=Phil |publisher=Bloomberg News |date=2008-11-24 |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081116003829/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=20601087 |archive-date=2008-11-16 |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登的儿子[[博·拜登|博·拜登]]由于即将随特拉华州陆军[[国民警卫队|国民警卫队]]在[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]服役，排除了自己在2008年挑选过程中的可能性。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/scorecard/1108/Minner_appoints_Ted_Kaufman_to_Biden_seat.html |title=Ted Kaufman to succeed Biden in Senate |last=Kraushaar |first=Josh |publisher=Politico |date=2008-11-24 |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-date=2009-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090124112431/http://www.politico.com/blogs/scorecard/1108/Minner_appoints_Ted_Kaufman_to_Biden_seat.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他曾是2010年特别选举的可能候选人，但在2010年初表示不会参选该席位。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/01/25/bidens-son-will-not-run-for-delaware-senate-seat/ |title=Biden's Son Will Not Run for Delaware's Open Senate Seat |last=Hulse |first=Carl |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2010-01-25 |accessdate=2010-01-25 |archive-date=2010-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100127063705/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/01/25/bidens-son-will-not-run-for-delaware-senate-seat/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]州长[[露丝·安·明纳|露丝·安·明纳]]宣布他将任命拜登的助手[[泰德·考夫曼|泰德·考夫曼]]接替拜登留下的参议员职位。<ref name="bloom112408" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ballotpedia.org/Ted_Kaufman|title=Ted Kaufman|website=Ballotpedia|access-date=2020-04-25|archive-date=2020-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200716115142/https://ballotpedia.org/Ted_Kaufman|dead-url=no}}</ref>在深情的告别仪式上，拜登对参议院成员说：“我在这里36年多的时间里，所看到的每一件好事，所迈出的每一个大胆的步伐，从未来自于[[利益團體|利益團體]]的施压，而来自[[人際關係|人際關係]]的成熟。”<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/15/biden-and-clinton-say-goodbye-to-senate |title=Biden and Clinton Say Goodbye to Senate |last=Becker |first=Bernie |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2009-01-15 |accessdate=2009-01-25 |archive-date=2009-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090121191827/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/15/biden-and-clinton-say-goodbye-to-senate/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

