拜登说，他打算取消[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]的副总统[[迪克·切尼|迪克·切尼]]所承担的一些角色，并不打算效仿以前任何一位副总统的做法。<ref name="lkl122208">{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/12/22/biden.lkl/index.html |title=Biden says he'll be different vice president |work=CNN |date=2008-12-22 |accessdate=2008-12-22 |archive-date=2008-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224093055/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/12/22/biden.lkl/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他主持了奥巴马的总统过渡团队<ref>{{cite news |title=Biden picks former Gore aide as chief of staff |work=Reuters |date=2008-11-13 |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/newsOne/idUSTRE4AC5EA20081113 |accessdate=2008-11-13 |first=Steve |last=Holland |archive-date=2009-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090103152957/http://www.reuters.com/article/newsOne/idUSTRE4AC5EA20081113 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，并领导了一项改善[[中產階級|中產階級]]经济福祉的倡议。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hornick|first1=Ed|last2=Levs|first2=Josh|date=2008-12-21|title=What Obama promised Biden|work=CNN|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/12/21/transition.wrap/index.html|accessdate=2008-12-23|archive-date=2008-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224052111/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/12/21/transition.wrap/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年1月初，在他作为参议院外交关系委员会主席的最后一次活动中，他会见了了[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]、[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]和[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]的领导人。<ref>{{cite news|last=Lee|first=Carol E.|date=2009-01-06|title='Senator' Biden's trip raises concerns|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2009/01/senator-bidens-trip-raises-concerns-017136|accessdate=2009-01-09|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194519/http://www.politico.com/story/2009/01/senator-bidens-trip-raises-concerns-017136|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年1月20日，拜登宣誓就任美国第47任副总统。<ref>{{cite news|date=2009-01-20|title=In culminating moment, Biden is vice president|work=OregonLive.com|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|url=https://www.oregonlive.com/politics/2009/01/in_culminating_moment_biden_is.html|accessdate=2016-07-27|archive-date=2020-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101194210/https://www.oregonlive.com/politics/2009/01/in_culminating_moment_biden_is.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他是第一位来自[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]的副总统<ref>{{cite news|date=2008-11-03|title=Think you know your election trivia?|work=CNN|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/11/03/election.trivia/index.html|accessdate=2008-11-09|archive-date=2008-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081106075757/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/11/03/election.trivia/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>和第一位[[天主教|天主教]]副总统。<ref name="npr2008">{{cite news|date=2009-01-09|title=The First Catholic Vice President?|agency=[[NPR|NPR]]|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/politicaljunkie/2009/01/the_first_catholic_vice_presid.html|accessdate=2019-09-25|archive-date=2019-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925060421/https://www.npr.org/sections/politicaljunkie/2009/01/the_first_catholic_vice_presid.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gaudiano|first=Nicole|date=2008-11-06|title=VP's home awaits if Biden chooses|work=The News Journal|url=http://www.delawareonline.com/article/20081106/NEWS02/811060379|accessdate=2008-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081109060406/http://www.delawareonline.com/article/20081106/NEWS02/811060379|archive-date=2008-11-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>

奥巴马很快就把拜登比作一个[[篮球运动员|篮球运动员]]，称“他做了很多数据表上显示不出的事。”<ref name="nyt032809">{{cite news|last=Leibovich|first=Mark|date=2009-03-28|title=Speaking Freely, Biden Finds Influential Role|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/29/us/politics/29biden.html|accessdate=2009-03-31|archive-date=2009-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090401232903/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/29/us/politics/29biden.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>5月，拜登访问[[科索沃|科索沃]]，再次肯定了美国对其“独立且不可逆转”的立场。<ref name="Chun9194">{{cite journal|last=Chun|first=Kwang-Ho|title=Kosovo: A New European Nation-State?|url=http://s-space.snu.ac.kr/bitstream/10371/96517/1/5.Kosovo-A-New-European-Nation-State_Kwang-ho-Chun.pdf|journal=Journal of International and Area Studies|volume=18|issue=1|year=2011|pages=91, 94|access-date=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082124/https://s-space.snu.ac.kr/bitstream/10371/96517/1/5.Kosovo-A-New-European-Nation-State_Kwang-ho-Chun.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登在向[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]扩充2.1万名兵力的内部辩论中输给了[[美国国务卿|国务卿]][[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]，<ref>{{cite news|last=Dilanian|first=Ken|date=2009-06-11|title=In a supporting role, Clinton takes a low-key approach at State Dept.|work=USA Today|url=https://www.usatoday.com/printedition/news/20090611/1aclinton11_cv.art.htm|accessdate=2009-07-22|archive-date=2011-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516020144/http://www.usatoday.com/printedition/news/20090611/1aclinton11_cv.art.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Smith|first=Ben|date=2009-06-23|title=Hillary Clinton toils in the shadows|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2009/06/clinton-toils-in-the-shadows-024067|accessdate=2009-07-22|archive-date=2015-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150916005405/http://www.politico.com/story/2009/06/clinton-toils-in-the-shadows-024067|dead-url=no}}</ref>但他对增兵所持的怀疑态度受到了重视，<ref name="pol091609" />随后在2009年，因奥巴马重新考虑其阿富汗战略，拜登的观点获得了更大的影响力。<ref name="nw-cov-1010092">{{cite news|last1=Bailey|first1=Holly|last2=Thomas|first2=Evan|date=2009-10-10|title=An Inconvenient Truth Teller|magazine=Newsweek|url=https://www.newsweek.com/joe-biden-white-house-truth-teller-81181|accessdate=2009-11-06|archive-date=2013-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123063731/http://www.newsweek.com/joe-biden-white-house-truth-teller-81181|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登约每两个月就会访问一次[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]，<ref name="nytm-traub" />成为了美国政府向伊拉克领导层传递有关伊拉克预期进展的联络人。<ref name="pol091609" />总地来说，监督伊拉克政策成为了拜登的责任，奥巴马则曾对拜登说：“-{zh-hans:乔;zh-tw:喬;zh-hk:祖}-，你负责伊拉克。”<ref>{{cite news|last=Osnos|first=Evan|date=2014-08-12|title=Breaking Up: Maliki and Biden|work=The New Yorker|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/daily-comment/breaking-maliki-biden|accessdate=2015-08-26|archive-date=2015-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151002053443/http://www.newyorker.com/news/daily-comment/breaking-maliki-biden|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登说，伊拉克“可能是本届政府的伟大成就之一”。<ref>{{cite news|date=2010-02-11|title=Vice President Biden: Iraq "Could Be One of the Great Achievements of This Administration"|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2010/02/vice-president-biden-iraq-could-be-one-of-the-great-achievements-of-this-administration/|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2015-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150223113546/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2010/02/vice-president-biden-iraq-could-be-one-of-the-great-achievements-of-this-administration/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他在2010年1月访问伊拉克时，正值因即将举行的伊拉克议会选举中的被禁候选人而引起的动荡。在他访问两天后，伊拉克政府就恢复了几百名候选人中的59名。<ref>{{cite news|date=2010-01-25|title=Iraq reinstates 59 election candidates|agency=[[Agence_France-Presse|Agence France-Presse]]|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iJGz55dJrnOzzejqmBj6QTolyydg|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2013-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320192516/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iJGz55dJrnOzzejqmBj6QTolyydg|dead-url=no}}</ref>截止2012年，拜登曾8次前往伊拉克，但随着2011年美军从伊拉克撤离，他对美国对伊拉克政策的监督力度有所减弱。<ref name="time-mo" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Crowley|first=Michael|date=2014-11-09|title=The war over President Obama's new war in Iraq|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2014/11/president-obama-war-iraq-112730|accessdate=2015-08-26|archive-date=2015-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151013002931/http://www.politico.com/story/2014/11/president-obama-war-iraq-112730|dead-url=no}}</ref>

