拜登还负责监督奥巴马的一揽子[[经济刺激|经济刺激]]计划中，旨在应对当前[[经济大衰退|经济衰退]]的[[基础设施|基础设施]]支出，并强调只有有价值的项目才能得到资金支持。<ref>{{cite news|last=Scherer|first=Michael|date=2009-07-01|title=What Happened to the Stimulus?|work=Time|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1908417,00.html|accessdate=2009-07-08|archive-date=2014-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109095116/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1908417,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他在这一角色中与数百名州长、市长和其他地方官员进行了交谈。<ref name="time-mo" />拜登对在此期间没有发生重大浪费或腐败事件感到满意<ref name="pol091609" />，当他在2011年2月完成这一职位时，他表示，利用经济刺激资金进行欺诈的事件仅占不到1%。<ref>{{cite news|last=Travers|first=Karen|date=2011-02-17|title='Sheriff Joe' Biden Touts Recovery Act Success—and Hands Over His Badge|publisher=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|url=http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/02/sheriff-joe-biden-touts-recovery-act-success-and-hands-over-his-badge.html|accessdate=2011-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221153327/http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/02/sheriff-joe-biden-touts-recovery-act-success-and-hands-over-his-badge.html|archive-date=2011-02-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2009年4月下旬，拜登在[[2009年H1N1流感大流行|H1N1流感爆发]]之初对一个问题脱口回答称，他会建议家人不要乘坐[[飛機|飛機]]或[[地鐵|地鐵]]，导致白宫迅速收回了这一言论。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Silva|first1=Mark|last2=Parsons|first2=Christi|date=2009-05-01|title=White House adjusts Biden's swine flu advice|work=Los Angeles Times|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-may-01-na-biden1-story.html|accessdate=2009-05-28|archive-date=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009170032/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-may-01-na-biden1-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>这句话让拜登的[[金斯利失言|大嘴巴]]名声再度兴起。<ref>{{cite news|date=2009-05-01|title=White House tempers Biden's swine flu advice|work=Boston Globe|url=https://www.boston.com/news/health/articles/2009/05/01/white_house_tempers_bidens_swine_flu_advice/|accessdate=2009-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090505114058/http://www.boston.com/news/health/articles/2009/05/01/white_house_tempers_bidens_swine_flu_advice/|archive-date=2009-05-05|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nw-cov-1010092"/><ref>{{cite news|last=Kurtzman|first=Daniel|date=2009-05-08|title=The Week's Best Late-Night Jokes|publisher=About.com|url=https://www.liveabout.com/late-night-political-jokes-2733896|accessdate=2009-05-28|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611193402/https://www.liveabout.com/late-night-political-jokes-2733896|dead-url=no}}</ref>面对2009年7月失业率上升的情况，拜登承认政府“误读了经济有多糟糕”，但他仍然相信，一旦支出步伐加快，经济刺激计划就会创造更多的就业机会。<ref>{{cite news|date=2009-07-05|title=Biden: 'We misread how bad the economy was'|publisher=[[NBC_News|NBC News]]|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31745563|accessdate=2009-07-09|archive-date=2013-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217104812/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31745563/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2010年3月23日，在面向全国的新闻直播中，一个[[麦克风|麦克风]]拾音到了拜登对奥巴马说，他签署《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|患者保护与平价医疗法案]]》是“他妈的大事”。[[白宫新闻秘书|白宫新闻秘书]]罗伯特·吉布斯（Robert Gibbs）后来在推特上回答说："是的，副总统先生，你说对了……"<ref name="bigdeal2">{{cite news|last=Herszenhorn|first=David M.|date=2010-03-23|title=At White House, Biden's Expletive Caught on Open Mic|magazine=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/23/at-white-house-bidens-expletive-caught-on-open-mic/|accessdate=2010-03-23|archive-date=2010-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325035208/http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/23/at-white-house-bidens-expletive-caught-on-open-mic/|dead-url=no}}</ref>尽管性格不同，奥巴马和拜登还是建立了友谊，部分原因是奥巴马的女儿萨沙（Sasha）和拜登的外孙女梅茜（Maisy）一起在西德韦尔友好学校上学。<ref name="nyt0508122"/>

奥巴马政府成员说，拜登在白宫的作用是作为一个对立面，迫使别人为自己的立场辩护。<ref name=":32">{{Cite news|last=Baker|first=Peter|date=2019-04-28|title=Biden and Obama's 'Odd Couple' Relationship Aged Into Family Ties|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/28/us/politics/barack-obama-biden.html|access-date=2020-04-26|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200606093422/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/28/us/politics/barack-obama-biden.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[白宮幕僚長|白宮幕僚長]]赫姆·伊曼纽尔（Rahm Emanuel）称，拜登帮助对抗[[群體思維|群體思維]]。<ref name="nyt032809" />[[白宫新闻秘书|白宫新闻秘书]]杰伊·卡尼（Jay Carney）是拜登的前通讯主管，他说拜登时常扮演了“情况室里的坏人”的角色。"<ref name=":32" />奥巴马的另一位高级顾问说，拜登“总是准备做家庭野餐时的[[臭鼬|臭鼬]]，以确保我们在智力上尽可能诚实。”<ref name="pol091609" />奥巴马说：“-{zh-hans:乔;zh-tw:喬;zh-hk:祖}-最好的一点是，当我们把大家聚在一起的时候，他真的会迫使人们思考和捍卫自己的立场，从多个角度看问题，这对我来说是非常有价值的。”<ref name="pol091609" />2010年6月11日，拜登代表美国出席了[[國際足協世界盃|國際足協世界盃]]开幕式，出席了英格兰对美国队的比赛，并访问了[[埃及|埃及]]、[[肯尼亚|肯尼亚]]和[[南非|南非]]。<ref>{{cite news|date=2010-06-12|title=Biden visits South Africa as World Cup begins|work=CNN|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2010/POLITICS/06/12/south.africa.biden/index.html|accessdate=2010-06-13|archive-date=2010-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100624070723/http://edition.cnn.com/2010/POLITICS/06/12/south.africa.biden/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登夫妇在华盛顿的官邸保持着轻松的气氛，经常招待孙子，并定期回到特拉华州的家中。<ref name="pol-regular">{{cite news|last=Parnes|first=Amie|date=2011-06-28|title=Joe and Jill Biden's 'regular' lives|newspaper=Politico|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2011/06/the-bidens-regular-lives-057887|accessdate=2011-06-28|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194519/http://www.politico.com/story/2011/06/the-bidens-regular-lives-057887|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登在2010年中期选举中大力为民主党助选，在预测民主党将大规模失利的情况下，仍保持乐观态度。<ref name="nyt1013102">{{cite news|last=Stolberg|first=Sheryl Gay|date=2010-10-12|title=Vice President Tries to Energize Democrats|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/13/us/politics/13biden.html|accessdate=2010-10-14|archive-date=2010-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028044617/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/13/us/politics/13biden.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在共和党在选举中大获全胜、白宫幕僚长拉赫姆·伊曼纽尔离职后，拜登过去与国会共和党人的关系变得更加重要，<ref name="pol1209102">{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Carol E.|last2=Bresnahan|first2=John|date=2010-12-09|title=Joe Biden expands role as White House link to Congress|newspaper=Politico|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2010/12/biden-steps-into-rahms-shoes-046173|accessdate=2010-12-10|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016194519/http://www.politico.com/story/2010/12/biden-steps-into-rahms-shoes-046173|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt1211102">{{cite news|last=Cooper|first=Helene|date=2010-12-11|title=As the Ground Shifts, Biden Plays a Bigger Role|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/12/us/politics/12biden.html|accessdate=2010-12-13|archive-date=2010-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101213044241/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/12/us/politics/12biden.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他领导政府成功地争取到参议院批准《[[新削减战略武器条约|新削减战略武器条约]]》。<ref name="pol1209102" /><ref name="nyt1211102" />2010年12月，拜登持中间立场，随后与参议院少数党领袖[[米奇·麥康諾|米奇·麥康諾]]进行谈判，对政府提出包括暂时延长布什减税政策在内的妥协性税收方案起到了重要作用。<ref name="nyt1211102" /><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Hulse|first1=Carl|last2=Calmes|first2=Jackie|date=2010-12-07|title=Biden and G.O.P. Leader Helped Hammer Out Bipartisan Tax Accord|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/08/us/politics/08deal.html|accessdate=2010-12-08|archive-date=2010-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208043606/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/08/us/politics/08deal.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后，拜登带头试图向国会中不情愿的民主党成员推销该协议。<ref name="nyt1211102" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Herszenhorn|first1=David M.|last2=Stolberg|first2=Sheryl Gay|date=2010-12-07|title=Democrats Skeptical of Obama on New Tax Plan|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/08/us/politics/08cong.html|accessdate=2010-12-08|archive-date=2011-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520053117/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/08/us/politics/08cong.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>最后该方案成功作为《{{Link-en|2010年税收减免、失业保险重新授权和创造就业法案|Tax Relief, Unemployment Insurance Reauthorization, and Job Creation Act of 2010}}》获得通过。<ref name="nyt1211102" />

2011年3月19日，为纪念拜登对[[美铁|美铁]]和美国铁路客运的支持的纪念，位于[[東北走廊|東北走廊]]上的[[威尔明顿站_(特拉华州)|威尔明顿站]]被命名为小约瑟夫·R·拜登车站。在拜登担任美国联邦参议员期间，他在本站和华府间乘坐火车超过7000次，<ref name="ajabc">{{cite news |url=http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/03/amtrak-joe-biden-gets-his-own-train-station.html |title='Amtrak Joe' Biden Gets His Own Train Station |author=Travers, Karen |publisher=[[ABC_News|ABC News]] |date=2011-03-16 |accessdate=2011-03-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319050955/http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/03/amtrak-joe-biden-gets-his-own-train-station.html |archivedate=2011-03-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.delawareonline.com/article/20110319/NEWS03/110319015/Biden-I-don-t-deserve-Amtrak-station-honor?odyssey=tab%7cmostpopular%7ctext%7cFRONTPAGE |title=Biden: 'I don't deserve' Amtrak station honor |author=Bothum, Kelly |newspaper=The News Journal |date=2011-03-19 |accessdate=2011-03-19 }}{{Dead link}}</ref>他也因与美铁的深厚历史而被称作“美铁-{zh-hans:乔;zh-tw:喬;zh-hk:祖}-”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Story Behind Joe Biden's "Amtrak Joe" Nickname|url=https://www.marieclaire.com/politics/a32363173/joe-biden-amtrak-joe-meaning/|accessdate=2020-12-25|date=2020-05-04|last=Igoe|first=Katherine J.|work=Marie Claire|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129094726/https://www.marieclaire.com/politics/a32363173/joe-biden-amtrak-joe-meaning/|dead-url=no}}</ref>同月，奥巴马委托拜登领导国会与白宫之间的谈判，以解决2011年余下时间的联邦预算，避免[[美國政府停擺|政府停擺]]。<ref>{{cite news|date=2011-03-02|title=Obama Welcomes Budget Deal; Biden to Lead Talks|publisher=[[CNBC|CNBC]]|agency=Reuters|url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/41870549|accessdate=2011-03-09|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120729195403/http://www.cnbc.com/id/41870549|archive-date=2012-07-29|dead-url=no}}</ref>2011年5月，由6名国会成员组成的“拜登小组”试图就提高美国债务上限达成两党协议，作为整体赤字消减计划的一部分。<ref>{{cite news|last=Reid|first=Tim|date=2011-05-16|title=Q+A: Debt and deficit talks in early stages|work=[[Reuters|Reuters]]|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/16/us-usa-debt-talks-idUSTRE74F26V20110516|accessdate=2011-05-17|archive-date=2011-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520004749/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/16/us-usa-debt-talks-idUSTRE74F26V20110516|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gaudiano|first=Nicole|date=2011-05-04|title=Biden tasked with achieving consensus on cutting deficit|newspaper=The News Journal|url=http://www.delawareonline.com/article/20110505/NEWS02/105050326/Biden-tasked-achieving-consensus-cutting-deficit?odyssey=tab%7Ctopnews%7Ctext%7CHome|accessdate=2011-05-17}}{{Dead link}}</ref>[[2011年美國債務上限危機|美國債務上限危機]]在接下来的几个月里继续，但拜登与[[米奇·麥康諾|米奇·麥康諾]]的关系再次被证明是打破僵局、促成达成解决协议的关键。该法案以2011年8月2日签署的《{{Link-en|2011年预算控制法案|Budget Control Act of 2011}}》的形式通过，在签署当天，美国前所未有的[[債務違約|債務違約]]已经迫在眉睫。<ref name="pol-bca2">{{cite news|last1=Thrush|first1=Glenn|last2=Brown|first2=Carrie Budoff|last3=Raju|first3=Manu|last4=Bresnahan|first4=John|date=2011-08-02|title=Joe Biden, Mitch McConnell and the making of a debt deal|newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]]|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2011/08/biden-mcconnell-and-the-making-of-a-deal-060463|accessdate=2011-08-04|archive-date=2015-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150922144250/http://www.politico.com/story/2011/08/biden-mcconnell-and-the-making-of-a-deal-060463|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ap-bca2">{{cite news|date=2011-08-03|title=The real drama was in private as debt deal hatched|work=[[Fox_News|Fox News]]|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/the-real-drama-was-in-private-as-debt-deal-hatched|accessdate=2011-08-04|archive-date=2019-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230142752/https://www.foxnews.com/us/the-real-drama-was-in-private-as-debt-deal-hatched|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Bohan|first1=Caren|last2=Sullivan|first2=Andy|last3=Ferraro|first3=Thomas|date=2011-08-03|title=Special report: How Washington took the U.S. to the brink|work=[[Reuters|Reuters]]|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-debt-brink/special-report-how-washington-took-the-u-s-to-the-brink-idUSTRE77271R20110803|accessdate=2011-08-04|archive-date=2017-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013231825/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-debt-brink/special-report-how-washington-took-the-u-s-to-the-brink-idUSTRE77271R20110803|dead-url=no}}</ref>在奥巴马政府中，拜登在债务问题上与国会讨价还价的时间是最多的。<ref name="ap-bca2" />一位共和党幕僚说：“拜登是唯一有真正谈判权力的人，麦康奈尔知道他的话算数。他是达成这笔交易的关键”。<ref name="pol-bca2" />

有报道称，拜登曾反对继续执行[[奥萨马·本·拉登之死|2011年5月美国击毙]][[奥萨马·本·拉登|奥萨马·本·拉登]]的任务，<ref name="time-mo" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Weigel|first=David|date=2014-01-10|title=Hillary Told the President That Her Opposition to the Surge in Iraq Had Been Political|work=Slate|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2014/01/robert-gates-duty-hillary-told-the-president-that-her-opposition-to-the-surge-in-iraq-had-been-political.html|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082441/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2014/01/robert-gates-duty-hillary-told-the-president-that-her-opposition-to-the-surge-in-iraq-had-been-political.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>以免可能的失败对奥巴马的连任前景造成不利影响。<ref>{{cite news|last=Thiessen|first=Marc A.|date=2012-10-08|title=Biden's Bin Laden Hypocrisy|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/marc-thiessen-bidens-bin-laden-hypocrisy/2012/10/08/990aca7c-114d-11e2-be82-c3411b7680a9_story.html|accessdate=2015-08-29|archive-date=2015-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904124649/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/marc-thiessen-bidens-bin-laden-hypocrisy/2012/10/08/990aca7c-114d-11e2-be82-c3411b7680a9_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Perks|first=Ashley|date=2018-06-01|title=Hillary Clinton's 'ass-covering' on bin Laden raid 'rattled' Biden|website=TheHill|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/390144-hillary-clintons-ass-covering-on-bin-laden-raid-rattled-biden|access-date=2019-04-29|archive-date=2019-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513134732/https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/390144-hillary-clintons-ass-covering-on-bin-laden-raid-rattled-biden|dead-url=no}}</ref>他后来带头将成功结果通知了国会领导人。<ref>{{cite news|date=2011-05-02|title=Osama Bin Laden dead; President Obama addresses nation|newspaper=Times Herald-Record|agency=NewsCore|url=https://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20110501/NEWS/110509984|accessdate=2011-05-17|archive-date=2011-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928012811/http://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20110501%2FNEWS%2F110509984|dead-url=no}}</ref>

