2010年10月，拜登表示，奥巴马要求他继续担任2012年总统大选的竞选搭档，<ref name="nyt1013102" />但由于奥巴马的人气在下降，[[白宮幕僚長|白宮幕僚長]][[威廉·M·戴利|威廉·戴利]]在2011年年底进行了一些秘密民调和研究，提出了用[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]取代拜登参选的想法，<ref name="nyt-dd-replace" />当结果显示奥巴马的情况没有明显改善时，这个想法就被放弃了，<ref name="nyt-dd-replace">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/01/us/politics/book-details-consideration-of-replacing-biden-on-2012-ticket.html |title=Book Details Obama Aides' Talks About Replacing Biden on 2012 Ticket |last=Martin |first=Jonathan |newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=2013-10-31 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082553/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/01/us/politics/book-details-consideration-of-replacing-biden-on-2012-ticket.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>白宫官员后来表示，奥巴马从未考虑过这个想法。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/politico44/2013/11/wh-obama-never-considered-dropping-joe-biden-176520 |title=W.H.: Obama never considered dropping Joe Biden |last=Allen |first=Jonathan |newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2013-11-01 |access-date=2013-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104143531/http://www.politico.com/politico44/2013/11/wh-obama-never-considered-dropping-biden-176520.html |archive-date=2013-11-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登在2012年5月发表声明，称他对[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]“绝对没问题”。拜登与奥巴马的立场相比获得了极大的关注，奥巴马的立场曾被描述为“不断演变”。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/la-xpm-2012-may-06-la-na-biden-gay-marriage-20120507-story.html |title=Biden 'comfortable' with equal rights for gays who wed |date=2012-05-06 |first=Christi |last=Parsons |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=2012-05-08 |archive-date=2019-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526082737/https://www.latimes.com/world/la-xpm-2012-may-06-la-na-biden-gay-marriage-20120507-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登在未经白宫同意的情况下发表声明令奥巴马和他的助手们相当恼火，因为奥巴马曾计划在几个月后的民主党代表大会筹备期间再转变立场，而且拜登此前曾劝告总统回避这一问题，以免冒犯关键的[[天主教|天主教]]选民。<ref name="nyt0508122" /><ref name="ap051012" /><ref name="pol-ebook">{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/politico-e-book-obama-campaign-roiled-by-conflict-079867 |title=Politico e-book: Obama campaign roiled by conflict |last=Thrush |first=Glenn |newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2012-08-20 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084846/https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/politico-e-book-obama-campaign-roiled-by-conflict-079867 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/6-hidden-obama-campaign-fault-lines-080028 |title=6 hidden fault lines in President Obama's campaign |last=Thursh |first=Glenn |newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2012-08-23 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2020-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208190849/https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/6-hidden-obama-campaign-fault-lines-080028 |dead-url=no }}</ref>同性恋权利倡导者立即抓住了拜登的声明，<ref name="ap051012" />几天内，奥巴马宣布他也支持同性婚姻，这一行动部分因拜登的意外言论所迫。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/10/us/politics/obama-says-same-sex-marriage-should-be-legal.html | title=Obama Says Same-Sex Marriage Should Be Legal | first1=Jackie | last1=Calmes | first2=Peter | last2=Baker | newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] | date=2012-05-09 | accessdate=2012-05-10 | archive-date=2012-05-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510014102/http://www.nytimes.com//2012/05/10/us/politics/obama-says-same-sex-marriage-should-be-legal.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登私下里为自己的发言向奥巴马道歉，<ref name="pol-ebook" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/10/joe-biden-gay-marriage-apology_n_1507939.html |title=Joe Biden Reportedly Apologized To Obama Over Gay Marriage Comments |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |work=Huffington Post |date=2012-05-10 |accessdate=2013-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130528233546/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/10/joe-biden-gay-marriage-apology_n_1507939.html |archive-date=2013-05-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>同时奥巴马公开称拜登的发言是发自内心的，<ref name="ap051012">{{cite news | url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/ap-source-biden-apologizes-to-obama-over-comments | title=AP source: Biden apologizes to Obama over comments | agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] | publisher=[[Fox_News|Fox News]] | date=2012-05-10 | accessdate=2012-05-16 | archive-date=2018-10-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006123920/https://www.foxnews.com/us/ap-source-biden-apologizes-to-obama-over-comments | dead-url=no }}</ref>这一事件表明，拜登有时仍无法控制自己的大嘴巴，<ref name="nyt0508122" />正如《[[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]]》所写：“每个人都知道拜登最大的优势也是他最大的弱点。”<ref name="time-mo" />双方的关系在拜登似乎在利用自己的地位为他可能的2016年总统竞选寻找筹款联系人时变得更为紧张，最终他被排除在奥巴马竞选团队的战略会议之外。<ref name="nyt-dd-replace" />

尽管如此，奥巴马竞选团队仍然十分看重拜登，认为他是一个能与心怀不满的蓝领工人和农村居民建立联系的政治家，随着2012年春季奥巴马连任竞选活动的正式开始，他在[[搖擺州|搖擺州]]的出场日程安排变得繁重。<ref name="time-be-joe" /><ref name="time-mo">{{cite news | title=Mo Joe | last=Scherer|first=Michael | magazine=Time | date=2012-06-11 | pages=26–30}}</ref>2012年8月，拜登在一位[[混血兒|混血]]听众面前说，共和党提出的放宽[[华尔街|华尔街]]监管的建议会“让你们重新戴上镣铐”，这让人们对拜登与人面对面的能力与他偏离轨道的倾向进行了分析。<ref name="time-be-joe" /><ref name="lat-offt" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/mission-impossible-managing-biden-079776 |title=Mission Impossible: Managing Joe Biden |last=Martin |first=Jonathan |newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2012-08-16 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084811/https://www.politico.com/story/2012/08/mission-impossible-managing-biden-079776 |dead-url=no }}</ref>《洛杉矶时报》写道：“大多数候选人都会反复说同样的言论，让记者甚至观众都想睡觉。但拜登任何一次演讲中，可能会出现十几个让负责媒体的幕僚们尴尬的时刻，并促使记者们既好笑又困惑地相互交谈。”<ref name="lat-offt">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2012-aug-17-la-na-biden-20120817-story.html |title=Biden's unscripted moments keep campaign on its toes |last=Memoli |first=Michael A. |newspaper=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]] |date=2012-08-17 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082611/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2012-aug-17-la-na-biden-20120817-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《时代杂志》写道，拜登经常走得太远，“除了令人熟悉的华盛顿政治家的需求性与过度自信的混合，拜登的大脑还是比一般的程度更傻。”<ref name="time-be-joe">{{cite news |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,2123322,00.html |title=Let There Be Joe |last=Von Drehle |first=David |magazine=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]] |date=2012-09-10 |pages=41–43 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109162947/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,2123322,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

拜登在9月举行的2012年民主党全国代表大会上被正式提名连任副总统。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/beau-biden-speech-read-th_n_1862997 |title=Beau Biden Speech Kicks Of Motion To Nominate Father Joe Biden For Vice President |work=Huffington Post |date=2012-09-06 |first=Elyse |last=Siegel |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082621/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/beau-biden-speech-read-th_n_1862997 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在10月11日的副总统辩论中，拜登在与[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]候选人[[保罗·瑞安|保罗·瑞安]]议员辩论时，对奥巴马政府的政绩进行了慷慨激昂的辩护，并对共和党的选举组合进行了有力的抨击。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nbcpolitics.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/10/11/14376267-biden-plays-aggressor-in-debate-as-ryan-argues-gop-case |title=Biden plays aggressor in debate as Ryan makes GOP case |last=O'Brien |first=Michael |publisher=[[NBC_News|NBC News]] |date=2012-10-11 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2020-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928140933/http://nbcpolitics.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/10/11/14376267-biden-plays-aggressor-in-debate-as-ryan-argues-gop-case |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/sparks-fly-as-biden-ryan-face-off-in-feisty-vice-presidential-debate | title=Sparks fly as Biden, Ryan face off in feisty vice presidential debate | publisher=[[Fox_News|Fox News]] | date=2012-10-11 | accessdate=2020-12-25 | archive-date=2021-01-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082631/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/sparks-fly-as-biden-ryan-face-off-in-feisty-vice-presidential-debate | dead-url=no }}</ref>11月6日，奥巴马和拜登以538张选举人票中的332张和51%的普选得票再次当选。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/obama-defeats-romney-to-win-second-term-vows-he-has-more-work-to-do | title=Obama defeats Romney to win second term, vows he has 'more work to do' | publisher=Fox News | date=2012-11-07 | accessdate=2020-12-25 | archive-date=2021-02-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215014622/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/obama-defeats-romney-to-win-second-term-vows-he-has-more-work-to-do | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/la-xpm-2013-jan-04-la-pn-obama-biden-officially-win-second-term-20130104-story.html |title=It's official: Obama, Biden win second term |last=Memoli |first=Michael A. |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2013-01-04 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082641/https://www.latimes.com/world/la-xpm-2013-jan-04-la-pn-obama-biden-officially-win-second-term-20130104-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2012年12月，奥巴马任命拜登为枪支暴力特别工作组负责人，该工作组在[[桑迪胡克小学枪击案|桑迪胡克小学枪击案]]后为解决美国[[槍械暴力|槍械暴力]]而设立。<ref name="Caldwell">{{cite news|last=Caldwell|first=Leigh Ann|date=2012-12-19|title=Obama sets up gun violence task force|publisher=[[CBS_News|CBS News]]|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/obama-sets-up-gun-violence-task-force/|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185454/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/obama-sets-up-gun-violence-task-force/|dead-url=no}}</ref>当月晚些时候，在美国跌落“[[美國財政懸崖|財政懸崖]]”前的最后几天，拜登与[[米奇·麥康諾|麥康諾]]的关系再次显现了其重要性，两人通过谈判达成了一项协议，导致《{{Link-en|2012年美国纳税人减免法案|American Taxpayer Relief Act of 2012}}》在2013年初得以通过，<ref>{{cite news |url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2013/jan/01/its-over-house-passes-fiscal-cliff-deal/ |title=It's over: House passes 'fiscal cliff' deal |last=Demirjian |first=Karoun |newspaper=Las Vegas Sun |date=2013-01-01 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185455/https://lasvegassun.com/news/2013/jan/01/its-over-house-passes-fiscal-cliff-deal/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ap-cliff">{{cite news |url=http://www.startribune.com/politics/national/185276422.html |title=Congress' OK of fiscal cliff deal gives Obama a win, prevents GOP blame for tax boosts |last=Fram |first=Alan |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |newspaper=Star Tribune |location=Minneapolis |date=2013-01-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130105020524/http://www.startribune.com/politics/national/185276422.html |archive-date=2013-01-05 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref>该法案将布什的许多减税措施永久化，但提高了高收入阶层的税率。<ref name="ap-cliff" />

