2013年1月20日，拜登在他的官邸举行小型仪式，由大法官[[索尼娅·索托马约尔|索尼娅·索托马约尔]]主持（1月21日举行了公开仪式），正式就任第二任期。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/20/us-usa-inauguration-biden-idUSBRE90J08B20130120 |title=Vice President Biden sworn into office for second term |last=Rampton |first=Roberta |work=Reuters |date=2013-01-20 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2013-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122062434/https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/20/us-usa-inauguration-biden-idUSBRE90J08B20130120 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>他继续站在立法最前线，在[[桑迪胡克小学枪击案|桑迪胡克小学枪击案]]发生后，奥巴马政府提出行政命令并提出新的枪支管制措施<ref name="time-cov-0113">{{cite news |url=http://swampland.time.com/2013/01/16/americas-new-gunfight-inside-the-campaign-to-avert-mass-shootings/ |title=The Next Gun Fight |last=Scherer |first=Michael |magazine=Time |date=2013-01-28 |accessdate=2020-12-17 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103081050/https://swampland.time.com/2013/01/16/americas-new-gunfight-inside-the-campaign-to-avert-mass-shootings/ |dead-url=no }} Cover story.</ref>（但这些措施未能通过）。<ref>{{cite news |last=Weisman |first=Jonathan |date=2013-04-17 |title=Senate Blocks Drive for Gun Control |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/04/18/us/politics/senate-obama-gun-control.html |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082704/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/04/18/us/politics/senate-obama-gun-control.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2013年10月通过《2014年持续拨款法案》的讨论中，拜登几乎没有参与，该法案解决了2013年联邦政府关门和2013年的债务上限危机。这因为参议院多数党领袖[[哈里·瑞德|哈里·瑞德]]和其他民主党领袖将他排除在与国会的任何直接谈判之外，他们觉得拜登在之前的谈判中透露了太多信息。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2013/10/anatomy-of-a-shutdown-098518 |title=Anatomy of a shutdown |last1=Bresnahan |first1=John |last2=Manu |first2=Raju |last3=Sherman |first3=Jake |last4=Brown |first4=Carrie Budoff |newspaper=Politico |date=2013-10-18 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185529/https://www.politico.com/story/2013/10/anatomy-of-a-shutdown-098518 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2013/10/13/biden-mostly-out-of-sight-during-shutdown-showdown/2968373/ |title=Biden mostly out of sight as shutdown drags on |last=Gaudiano |first=Nicole |newspaper=USA Today |date=2013-10-13 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082716/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2013/10/13/biden-mostly-out-of-sight-during-shutdown-showdown/2968373/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/biden-takes-back-seat-in-budget-negotiations-during-shutdown | title=Biden takes a back seat during budget negotiations over shutdown | last=Bowman | first=Bridget | work=PBS NewsHour | publisher=PBS | date=2013-10-14 | accessdate=2020-12-25 | archive-date=2021-01-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082723/https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/biden-takes-back-seat-in-budget-negotiations-during-shutdown | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年，拜登的《暴力侵害妇女法》再次得到授权。该法案导致了一系列进展，如在拜登第一任期成立的白宫妇女和女孩委员会，以及2014年1月成立的由拜登和瓦莱丽·贾雷特（Valerie Jarrett）担任联合主席的白宫保护学生免受性侵犯特别工作组。<ref name="Report">{{cite web |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/docs/sexual_assault_report_1-21-14.pdf |archive-url=https://archive.today/20160824035035/https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/docs/sexual_assault_report_1-21-14.pdf |archive-date=2016-08-24 |title=Rape and sexual assault: A renewed call to action |publisher=The White House |date=January 2014 |accessdate=2016-08-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite press release | url=https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2014/01/22/memorandum-establishing-white-house-task-force-protect-students-sexual-a | title=Memorandum: Establishing White House Task Force to Protect Students from Sexual Assault | publisher=obamawhitehouse.archives.gov | date=2014-01-22 | accessdate=2014-06-10 | archive-date=2017-01-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122115707/https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2014/01/22/memorandum-establishing-white-house-task-force-protect-students-sexual-a | dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登在[[新罕布什尔大学|新罕布什尔大学]]发表演讲时讨论了大学校园性侵犯相关的联邦指导方针。他说：“不管你喝醉了还是意識清醒，不同意就是不同意。不管你在床上还是在宿舍里，抑或在街上，不同意就是不同意。即使你一开始说同意，但隨後改变主意，不同意就是不同意。不同意就是不同意。”<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hayes|first=Dianne|year=2012|title=Looking The Other Way?|journal=Diverse: Issues in Higher Education}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Elaine Grant |title=Federal Effort Targets Sexual Assaults At Colleges |url=https://www.npr.org/2011/04/05/135135544/federal-effort-targets-sexual-assaults-at-colleges |accessdate=2019-04-05 |work=National Public Radio NPR |date=2011-04-05 |quote=BIDEN: Look, guys, no matter what a girl does, no matter how she's dressed, no matter how much she's had to drink, it's never, never, never, never, never OK to touch her without her consent. |archive-date=2019-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405205021/https://www.npr.org/2011/04/05/135135544/federal-effort-targets-sexual-assaults-at-colleges |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ashe Schow |title=Biden Reaps the #MeToo Whirlwind |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-reaps-the-metoo-whirlwind-11554419738 |accessdate=2019-04-05 |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=2019-04-04 |quote=While speaking to students at the University of New Hampshire in 2011, then-Vice President Joe Biden told men in the audience that 'no matter what a girl does, no matter how she's dressed, no matter how much she's had to drink—it's never, never, never, never, never OK to touch her without her consent.' |archive-date=2019-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405063733/https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-reaps-the-metoo-whirlwind-11554419738 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

