拜登赞成為叙利亚的反叛战士提供裝備。<ref>{{cite news |title=Who to Blame If Arming the Syrian Rebels Goes Wrong |first=Conor |last=Friedersdorf |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2014/09/who-to-blame-if-arming-syrian-rebels-goes-wrong/380411/ |work=The Atlantic |date=2014-09-18 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2019-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190512184447/https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2014/09/who-to-blame-if-arming-syrian-rebels-goes-wrong/380411/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2014年期间，随着伊拉克的分崩离析，人们重新关注2006年拜登·盖尔布的伊拉克联邦化计划，一些观察家认为拜登一直都是对的。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.politico.com/story/2014/06/joe-biden-iraq-107858 | title=Was Joe Biden right? | last=Gerstein | first=Josh | newspaper=Politico | date=2014-06-13 | accessdate=2014-09-14 | archive-date=2015-09-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927001111/http://www.politico.com/story/2014/06/joe-biden-iraq-107858 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nationaljournal.com/s/62830 |title=Turns Out, Joe Biden Was Right About Dividing Iraq |last=Kitfield |first=James |magazine=National Journal |date=2014-01-30 |accessdate=2014-09-14 |archive-date=2017-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011194233/https://www.nationaljournal.com/s/62830 |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登本人表示，美国将追着[[伊斯兰国|伊斯兰国]]“进入地狱之门”。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/Decoder/2014/0903/Joe-Biden-vows-to-chase-Islamic-State-to-gates-of-hell.-Does-he-mean-it |title=Joe Biden vows to chase Islamic State to 'gates of hell'. Does he mean it? |last=Grier |first=Peter |newspaper=The Christian Science Monitor |date=2014-09-03 |accessdate=2014-09-14 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185455/https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/Decoder/2014/0903/Joe-Biden-vows-to-chase-Islamic-State-to-gates-of-hell.-Does-he-mean-it |dead-url=no }}</ref>2013年12月，拜登在兒子[[亨特·拜登|亨特·拜登]]的陪同下訪問中國。2014年4月，拜登出訪[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]，再次呼籲烏克蘭增加天然氣生產。<ref name="wp20190722">{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/as-vice-president-biden-said-ukraine-should-increase-gas-production-then-his-son-got-a-job-with-a-ukrainian-gas-company/2019/07/21/f599f42c-86dd-11e9-98c1-e945ae5db8fb_story.html |script-title=en:In Hunter Biden’s career from Ukraine to China, his father is often nearby |publisher=The Washington Post |date=2019-07-22 |accessdate=2020-09-03 |archive-date=2020-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022090429/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/as-vice-president-biden-said-ukraine-should-increase-gas-production-then-his-son-got-a-job-with-a-ukrainian-gas-company/2019/07/21/f599f42c-86dd-11e9-98c1-e945ae5db8fb_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2015年12月8日，拜登在基辅的乌克兰议会发表讲话，<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_x9mT9jfzvw|title=Joe Biden english speech in Ukraine's parliament in Kiev|via=[[YouTube|YouTube]]|date=2015-12-08|accessdate=2015-12-08|archive-date=2022-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220506013617/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_x9mT9jfzvw}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/ukraine-politics/vice-president-joe-bidens-dec-8-speech-to-ukraines-parliament-403800.html |title=U.S. Vice President Joe Biden's Dec. 8 speech to Ukraine's parliament (VIDEO, TRANSCRIPT) |publisher=kyivpost.com |date=2015-12-08 |accessdate=2015-12-08 |archive-date=2015-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209155834/http://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/ukraine-politics/vice-president-joe-bidens-dec-8-speech-to-ukraines-parliament-403800.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>这是他多次对乌克兰访问之一，以确定美国对乌克兰的援助和政策立场。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2018-01-25/how-ukraine-s-president-fooled-joe-biden|title=How Ukraine's President Fooled Joe Biden|last=Bershidsky|first=Leonid|date=2018-01-25|work=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-01-30|archive-date=2018-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180130120945/https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2018-01-25/how-ukraine-s-president-fooled-joe-biden|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=COMMITTEE ON FOREIGN RELATIONS UNITED STATES SENATE|url=https://www.foreign.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/03%2015%2016%20Ukrainian%20Reforms%20Two%20Years%20After%20the%20Maidan%20Revolution%20and%20the%20Russian%20Invasion.pdf|access-date=2020-07-21|archive-date=2019-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119210006/https://www.foreign.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/03%2015%2016%20Ukrainian%20Reforms%20Two%20Years%20After%20the%20Maidan%20Revolution%20and%20the%20Russian%20Invasion.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登与多位拉美领导人关系密切，并在执政期间被指派关注该地区。他在副总统任期内访问该地区16次，是所有总统或副总统中最多的。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Paz|first=Christian|date=2020-10-26|title=The Biden Doctrine Begins With Latin America|work=The Atlantic|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2020/10/joe-biden-foreign-policy-latin-america/616841/|access-date=2020-11-15|issn=1072-7825|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111041523/https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2020/10/joe-biden-foreign-policy-latin-america/616841/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年2月17日，在新任國防部長[[阿什顿·卡特|阿什顿·卡特]]的宣誓儀式上，拜登站在卡特妻子斯蒂芬尼身後，把雙手放在她的雙肩上，又把鼻靠近她的頭髮，引起熱議。斯蒂芬妮·卡特称这些照片具有误导性，是在老朋友之间较长互动时提取出来的。卡特说，她对照片被滥用感到失望。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Wife of former Defense secretary calls photo with Biden misleading|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/wife-of-former-defense-secretary-calls-photo-with-biden-misleading|accessdate=2020-12-14|date=2019-04-01|last=DeMarche|first=Edmund|work=Fox News|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082838/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/wife-of-former-defense-secretary-calls-photo-with-biden-misleading|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登也被指在2015年1月參議員宣誓儀式的合照時段對參議員库恩斯的女兒玛姬有過分親近的舉止而引發爭議。但库恩斯很快澄清称他的女儿并不觉得拜登有过分行为。库恩斯称拜登当时向前俯身低声告诉玛姬说，当拜登宣誓就职时，他13岁的女儿阿什利也觉得很尴尬和不自在，拜登只不过在鼓励她如何度过在众人注视和媒体镜头下的一天。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Biden allegations revive scrutiny over history of 'uncomfortable' interactions with women|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-allegations-revive-scrutiny-over-history-of-uncomfortable-interactions-with-women|accessdate=2020-12-14|date=2019-04-01|last=O'Reilly|first=Andrew|work=Fox News|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116035946/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-allegations-revive-scrutiny-over-history-of-uncomfortable-interactions-with-women|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年，众议院议长[[约翰·博纳|约翰·博纳]]和参议院多数党领袖[[米奇·麦康奈尔|米奇·麦康奈尔]]在没有通知奥巴马政府的情况下，邀请以色列总理[[本雅明·内塔尼亚胡|本雅明·内塔尼亚胡]]在国会联席会议上发言。这种无视礼节的做法导致拜登和50多名国会民主党人跳过了内塔尼亚胡的演讲。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2015/02/26/politics/democrats-missing-netanyahu-whip-list/index.html|title=The list of Democrats skipping Netanyahu's speech|first=Alexandra|last=Jaffe|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-26|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818185113/https://www.cnn.com/2015/02/26/politics/democrats-missing-netanyahu-whip-list/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2016年8月，拜登访问[[塞尔维亚|塞尔维亚]]，在那里他会见了塞尔维亚总统[[亚历山大·武契奇|亚历山大·武契奇]]，并对[[科索沃战争|科索沃战争]]期间轰炸战役中的平民受害者表示慰问。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Melander |first1=Ingrid |title=Biden offers condolences for Serbs killed in 1999 NATO air strikes |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-balkans-biden-serbia/biden-offers-condolences-for-serbs-killed-in-1999-nato-air-strikes-idUSKCN10R1ZD |work=Reuters |date=2016-08-16 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185455/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-balkans-biden-serbia/biden-offers-condolences-for-serbs-killed-in-1999-nato-air-strikes-idUSKCN10R1ZD |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[科索沃|科索沃]]，他出席了以他儿子博的名字命名一条高速公路的仪式，以纪念博在培训科索沃法官和检察官方面为该国所做出的贡献。<ref name="Bytyci">{{cite news|last=Bytyci|first=Fatos|title='We owe you so much,' Kosovo to tell Biden as street named after late son|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kosovo-biden-street-idUSKCN10Q17X|work=Reuters|date=2016-08-15|accessdate=2020-10-24|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115185456/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kosovo-biden-street-idUSKCN10Q17X|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Bezhan">{{cite news|last=Bezhan|first=Frud|title=Word On The Street Is That Kosovo Has A Love Affair With Americans|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/kosovo-love-affair-americans-biden-clinton-bush/27928807.html|agency=Radio Free Europe / Radio Liberty|date=2016-08-17|accessdate=2020-10-24|archive-date=2020-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023065019/https://www.rferl.org/a/kosovo-love-affair-americans-biden-clinton-bush/27928807.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="RuViDeBi">{{cite news|last1=Rucker|first1=Philip|last2=Viser|first2=Matt|last3=DeBonis|first3=Mike|title=Trump and allies resume attacks on Biden's son as the Democrat surges|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-and-allies-resume-attacks-on-bidens-son-as-the-democrat-surges/2020/03/05/cad7fa02-5eed-11ea-b29b-9db42f7803a7_story.html|agency=The Washington Post|date=2020-03-06|accessdate=2020-10-24|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028094653/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-and-allies-resume-attacks-on-bidens-son-as-the-democrat-surges/2020/03/05/cad7fa02-5eed-11ea-b29b-9db42f7803a7_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登在任副总统期间，从未在参议员投出过打破平局的票，使他成为获此殊荣时间最长的副总统。<ref>{{cite web|last=Bycoffe|first=Aaron|date=2017-02-07|title=Pence Has Already Done Something Biden Never Did: Break A Senate Tie|url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/pence-has-already-done-something-biden-never-did-break-a-senate-tie/|website=FiveThirtyEight|quote=Twelve vice presidents, including Biden, never broke a tie; Biden was the longest-serving vice president to never do so.|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082937/https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/pence-has-already-done-something-biden-never-did-break-a-senate-tie/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年1月，拜登在卸任前夕獲奧巴馬頒授國民最高榮譽的[[總統自由勳章|總統自由勳章]]，感動得當場流淚。<ref>{{Cite web|title=【奧巴馬倒數】授「總統自由勳章」 拜登灑下男兒淚 ｜ 蘋果日報|url=https://hk.appledaily.com/international/20170113/Y5HVZCB67JILOSUTLVRJH2FRLM/|accessdate=2020-12-14|work=Apple Daily 蘋果日報|language=zh-hk|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082929/https://hk.appledaily.com/international/20170113/Y5HVZCB67JILOSUTLVRJH2FRLM/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他与歐巴馬之間情誼密切、合作無間，稱呼彼此為「好兄弟」，<ref>{{Cite web|title=奧巴馬與拜登，未走已令人想念的一對|url=https://www.thenewslens.com/article/54059|accessdate=2020-12-14|date=2016-11-14|last=周雪君|work=The News Lens 關鍵評論網|language=zh-TW|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082954/https://www.thenewslens.com/article/54059|dead-url=no}}</ref>並誓言對其畢生支持。<ref>{{Cite web|title=拜登竟被歐巴馬惹哭了：總統先生，只要一息尚存，我都會支持你|url=https://www.thenewslens.com/article/59227|accessdate=2020-12-14|date=2017-01-13|last=周雪君|work=The News Lens 關鍵評論網|language=zh-TW|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082943/https://www.thenewslens.com/article/59227|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 2016年总统选举 ===

[[File:VP_Biden_with_Pence.jpg|thumb]]会面]]

2014年2月7日，美国副总统拜登7日接受美国媒体访问时坦言，称他看不出什么明显的原因，让其不参加[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美國總統選舉]]的角逐。拜登在接受[[美国有线电视新闻网|美国有线电视新闻网]]访问时说，他将在2015年夏季作出正式决定。拜登表示，他将根据对自己的评估作出决定——他是否是最有资格治理国家的人。“这并不意味着我是唯一一个符合条件的人”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=拜登称无明显理由阻止其参加2016总统选举-中新网|url=http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2014/02-07/5809932.shtml|accessdate=2020-12-14|work=www.chinanews.com|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103082942/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2014/02-07/5809932.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>在他的第二个副总统任期内，拜登经常被说成是在为可能在为参加2016年民主党总统提名做准备。<ref name=Itkowitz1 />在2015年年中，他的家人、许多朋友和捐助者都鼓励他参加竞选，而当时[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]的支持率也在下降。据报道称拜登曾认真考虑参选，一个名作2016提名拜登（Draft Biden 2016）的[[政治行動委員會|政治行动委员会]]也注册成立。<ref name=Itkowitz1>{{cite news |first=Colby |last=Itkowitz |title=There is a 'Draft Joe Biden' Super PAC Now; It's Even Hiring a Fundraiser |newspaper=Washington Post |date=2015-03-23 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/in-the-loop/wp/2015/03/23/job-opening-raise-money-to-draft-joe-biden-to-run-in-2016/ |accessdate=2015-08-02 |archive-date=2015-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716011912/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/in-the-loop/wp/2015/03/23/job-opening-raise-money-to-draft-joe-biden-to-run-in-2016/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Dowd1>{{cite news |first=Maureen |last=Dowd |title=Joe Biden in 2016: What Would Beau Do? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/opinion/sunday/maureen-dowd-joe-biden-in-2016-what-would-beau-do.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2015-08-01 |accessdate=2020-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106105547/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/opinion/sunday/maureen-dowd-joe-biden-in-2016-what-would-beau-do.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first1=Jeff |last1=Zeleny |first2=Kevin |last2=Liptak |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2015/07/31/politics/vice-president-joe-biden-presidential-elections/ |title=Joe Biden Keeps Watchful Eye on 2016 Race |work=CNN |date=2015-08-01 |accessdate=2015-08-02 |archive-date=2016-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202185430/http://edition.cnn.com/2015/07/31/politics/vice-president-joe-biden-presidential-elections/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

到了2015年9月11日，拜登仍不确定是否要参选，他称儿子最近的去世极大地消耗了他的感情和能量，并说：“没有人有权利……去寻求那个职位，除非他们愿意把自己的110%奉献给它。”<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34216117|title=Joe Biden still undecided on presidential run|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|date=2015-09-11|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083021/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34216117|dead-url=no}}</ref>10月21日，拜登在妻子和奥巴马的陪伴下於玫瑰园的讲台上宣布他不会参加2016年总统竞选的决定。<ref>{{cite news |first=Jeff |last=Mason |url=https://www.aol.com/article/2015/10/21/biden-announces-hes-not-running-for-president/21252056/ |title=Biden says he will not seek 2016 Democratic nomination |agency=Thomson Reuters |date=2015-10-21 |accessdate=2015-10-21 |website=aol.com |archive-date=2015-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022211907/http://www.aol.com/article/2015/10/21/biden-announces-hes-not-running-for-president/21252056/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Comment Joe Biden Is Not Running For President In 2016|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/joe-biden-president-2016_n_55f1cefbe4b093be51be0d69|work=Huffington Post|accessdate=2015-10-21|archive-date=2019-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405213056/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/joe-biden-president-2016_n_55f1cefbe4b093be51be0d69|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Joe Biden Decides Not to Enter Presidential Race|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-decides-not-to-enter-presidential-race-1445444657|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2015-10-21|archive-date=2015-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151021204730/http://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-decides-not-to-enter-presidential-race-1445444657|dead-url=no}}</ref>2016年1月，拜登称确认其觉得这是正确的决定，但承认“每天都有后悔没有竞选总统”。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fabian|first1=Jordan|title=Biden regrets not running for president 'every day'|url=https://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/265011-biden-regrets-not-running-but-calls-it-right-decision|accessdate=2017-01-12|work=TheHill|date=2016-01-06|archive-date=2017-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102173755/http://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/265011-biden-regrets-not-running-but-calls-it-right-decision|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年6月9日，奥巴马宣布支持希拉里·克林顿，同日稍晚拜登也宣布对她的支持。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/joe-biden-endorses-hillary-clinton-224162|title=Joe Biden endorses Hillary Clinton|publisher=[[Politico|Politico]]|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083139/https://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/joe-biden-endorses-hillary-clinton-224162|dead-url=no}}</ref>在整个2016年大选期间，拜登一直在强烈批评克林顿的对手[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]，并经常用很生动多彩的词语来形容他。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/joe-biden-to-slam-donald-trump-in-speech-monday/|title=Joe Biden slams Donald Trump on wall, Muslim entry ban|date=2016-06-20|publisher=CBS News|first=Rebecca|last=Shabad|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083051/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/joe-biden-to-slam-donald-trump-in-speech-monday/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/biden-wishes-trump-gym-groping-comments/story?id=42965866|title=Biden Says He Wishes He Could Take Trump 'Behind the Gym' Over Groping Comments|date=2016-10-21|publisher=ABC|first=Maryalice|last=Parks|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083055/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/biden-wishes-trump-gym-groping-comments/story?id=42965866|dead-url=no}}</ref>

