[[File:Joe_Biden_(49536511763).jpg|thumb]]]]

在2016年至2019年间，媒体常将拜登视作2020年可能的总统候选人<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/politics/trailguide/la-na-trailguide-updates-201612-htmlstory.html#joe-biden-wouldnt-count-out-a-2020-run-for-president-but-he-was-asked-in-an-emotional-moment |title=Joe Biden wouldn't count out a 2020 run for president. But he was asked in an emotional moment |work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=2016-12-05 |date=2016-12-05 |last=Memoli |first=Michael |archive-date=2020-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620143719/https://www.latimes.com/nation/politics/trailguide/la-na-trailguide-updates-201612-htmlstory.html#joe-biden-wouldnt-count-out-a-2020-run-for-president-but-he-was-asked-in-an-emotional-moment |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当问及是否有意参选时，拜登给出了多种模糊的回答，称“莫言决不”（never say never）<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2016/12/07/politics/joe-biden-colbert-interview-2020-buzz/ |title=Biden stokes 2020 buzz on Colbert: 'Never say never' |work=CNN |accessdate=2016-12-08 |date=2016-12-07 |last=Wright |first=David |archive-date=2020-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620090156/https://edition.cnn.com/2016/12/07/politics/joe-biden-colbert-interview-2020-buzz// |dead-url=no }}</ref>，并一度表示看不到会让他再次参选的局面<ref>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/4593693/joe-biden-stephen-colbert-2020-run/ |title=Joe Biden Discussed Running in 2020 With Stephen Colbert: 'Never Say Never' |work=Time Magazine |accessdate=2016-12-08 |date=2016-12-07 |last=Lang |first=Cady |archive-date=2016-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161208083645/http://time.com/4593693/joe-biden-stephen-colbert-2020-run/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Revesz">{{cite news|last=Revesz|first=Rachael|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/joe-biden-think-tank-research-centre-university-pennsylvania-delaware-white-house-staff-cancer-a7526881.html|title=Joe Biden: I will not run for president in 2020 but I am working to cure cancer|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|date=2017-01-13|access-date=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116185058/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/joe-biden-think-tank-research-centre-university-pennsylvania-delaware-white-house-staff-cancer-a7526881.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，然而数日后表示“我能走就会参选”（I'll run if I can walk.）<ref name="IfICanWalk">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/17/magazine/joe-biden-i-wish-to-hell-id-just-kept-saying-the-exact-same-thing.html|title=Joe Biden: 'I Wish to Hell I'd Just Kept Saying the Exact Same Thing'|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|last=Alter|first=Jonathan|date=2017-01-17|accessdate=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121233919/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/17/magazine/joe-biden-i-wish-to-hell-id-just-kept-saying-the-exact-same-thing.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年1月，一个名为拜登时间到（Time for Biden）的[[政治行動委員會|政治行動委員會]]成立，旨在寻求拜登参选<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wvik.org/post/new-quad-city-super-pac-time-biden |title=New Quad City Super PAC: "Time for Biden" |last=Charnetzki |first=Tori |publisher=WVIK |date=2018-01-10 |accessdate=2018-01-24 |archive-date=2020-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620090209/https://www.wvik.org/post/new-quad-city-super-pac-time-biden/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

拜登表示最晚会在2019年一月决定是否参选<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2018/07/17/joe-biden-president-january-decision/793771002/ |first=Christal |last=Hayes |title=Joe Biden says he will decide whether he's running for president by January |work=USA Today |access-date=2018-07-18 |date=2018-07-17 |archive-date=2020-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620090212/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2018/07/17/joe-biden-president-january-decision/793771002// |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但最终并未宣布。其友人称其“非常接近要参选”，但担心再次竞选总统可能会对其家庭和声誉的影响，以及筹款的挑战和对他的年龄与相对中间派立场的看法<ref name="bidenclose">{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2019/02/joe-biden-close-running-president-despite-doubts/581956/ |title=Biden's Anguished Search for a Path to Victory |work=The Atlantic |access-date=2019-02-09 |date=2019-02-04 |first=Edward-Isaac |last=Dovere |archive-date=2020-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620090215/https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2019/02/joe-biden-close-running-president-despite-doubts/581956// |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另一方面，其参选的动机包括其“义务感”、反感特朗普的总统任期、其他可能参选的民主党人在外交政策方面缺乏经验、以及希望在党内培养“架起桥梁的进步主义”<ref name=bidenclose />。他于2019年4月25日宣布参选<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/former-vice-president-joe-biden-jumps-into-white-house-race/2019/04/25/093ff596-0aef-11e9-88e3-989a3e456820_story.html |title=Former vice president Joe Biden jumps into White House race |last1=Scherer |first1=Michael |date=2019-04-25 |work=The Washington Post |access-date=2019-04-25 |last2=Wagner |first2=John |archive-date=2020-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526072655/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/former-vice-president-joe-biden-jumps-into-white-house-race/2019/04/25/093ff596-0aef-11e9-88e3-989a3e456820_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 竞选期间 ===
2019年9月，报道称特朗普曾施压[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]总统[[弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基|弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基]]调查特朗普方面未有凭据主张的拜登和其子[[亨特·拜登|亨特·拜登]]的不当行为<ref name="pressure">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/20/world/europe/ukraine-trump-zelensky.html|title=Ukraine Pressured on U.S. Political Investigations|last=Kramer|first=Andrew E.|date=2019-09-20|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-09-20|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2019-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920171010/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/20/world/europe/ukraine-trump-zelensky.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，尽管尚无任何证据表明拜登一家有任何不当行为<ref>{{cite news |last=Isachenkov |first=Vladimir |title=Ukraine's prosecutor says there is no probe into Biden |url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/ukraines-prosecutor-says-there-is-no-probe-into-biden |accessdate=2019-10-01 |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |date=2019-09-27 |quote=Though the timing raised concerns among anti-corruption advocates, there has been no evidence of wrongdoing by either the former vice president or his son. |archive-date=2019-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001005328/https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/ukraines-prosecutor-says-there-is-no-probe-into-biden |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=White House 'tried to cover up details of Trump-Ukraine call' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-49842895 |accessdate=2019-10-01 |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |date=2019-09-26 |quote=There is no evidence of any wrongdoing by the Bidens. |archive-date=2019-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930105132/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-49842895 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Timm |first=Jane |title=There's no evidence for Trump's Biden-Ukraine accusations. What really happened? |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/there-s-no-evidence-trump-s-biden-ukraine-accusations-what-n1057851 |accessdate=2019-10-01 |work=[[NBC_News|NBC News]] |date=2019-09-25 |quote=But despite Trump's continued claims, there's no evidence of wrongdoing on the part of either Biden. |archive-date=2019-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001005034/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/there-s-no-evidence-trump-s-biden-ukraine-accusations-what-n1057851 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。媒体广泛认为，施压调查拜登一家是为了损害拜登当选总统的机会，因而引发一桩[[特朗普-乌克兰丑闻|政治丑闻]]<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-defends-conversation-with-ukraine-leader-11568993176 |date=2019-09-21 |title=Trump Repeatedly Pressed Ukraine President to Investigate Biden's Son |last3=Volz |first1=Alan |last1=Cullison |first2=Rebecca |last2=Ballhaus |first3=Dustin |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |access-date=2019-09-20 |archive-date=2019-09-21 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190921014320/https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-defends-conversation-with-ukraine-leader-11568993176 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2019/09/20/is-trump-trying-to-get-ukraine-to-take-out-biden-for-him/ |date=2019-09-20 |title=Is Trump Trying to Get Ukraine to Take Out Biden for Him? |last=Mackinnon |first=Amy |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=2019-09-20 |archive-date=2019-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920210034/https://foreignpolicy.com/2019/09/20/is-trump-trying-to-get-ukraine-to-take-out-biden-for-him/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，并导致众议院将[[第一次川普彈劾案|特朗普弹劾]]。

从2019年开始，特朗普及其盟友谬控拜登将乌克兰检察长{{link-en|維克多·肖金|Viktor Shokin}}出于对亨特·拜登受雇的{{link-en|布利斯瑪股份公司|Burisma Holdings}}进行调查而开除，并指控其从乌克兰扣留了10亿美元的援助。实际上，2015年，因为美国、欧盟和其他国际组织认为肖金腐败无能，尤其是因为肖金并未坚定地调查布利斯瑪，拜登向乌克兰议会施压，要求其撤下肖金，而扣留10亿美元的援助是这项官方政策的一部分<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2019/oct/11/donald-trump/trump-ad-misleads-about-biden-ukraine-and-prosecut/|title=PolitiFact—Donald Trump ad misleads about Joe Biden, Ukraine and the prosecutor|website=@politifact|accessdate=2020-11-08|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111194554/https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2019/oct/11/donald-trump/trump-ad-misleads-about-biden-ukraine-and-prosecut/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/09/27/quick-guide-trumps-false-claims-about-ukraine-bidens/|title=Analysis | A quick guide to President Trump's false claims about Ukraine and the Bidens|first=Glenn|last=Kessler|date=2019-09-27|website=Washington Post|accessdate=2020-11-08|archive-date=2020-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114222235/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/09/27/quick-guide-trumps-false-claims-about-ukraine-bidens/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/23/politics/fact-check-trump-ukraine-hunter-biden-joe-biden/index.html|title=Fact check: What Trump has been getting wrong on Biden and Ukraine|first=Daniel|last=Dale|website=CNN|accessdate=2020-11-08|archive-date=2020-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120000522/https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/23/politics/fact-check-trump-ukraine-hunter-biden-joe-biden/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>在2016年3月向[[美国参议院外交委员会|美国参议院外交委员会]]作证时，前驻[[乌克兰|乌克兰]][[大使|大使]]约翰·赫伯斯特说："By late fall of 2015, the EU and the United States joined the chorus of those seeking Mr. Shokin's removal" and that Joe Biden "spoke publicly about this before and during his December visit to Kyiv."在同一听证会上，助理[[美国国务卿|国务卿]][[卢岚_(美国外交官)|卢岚]]说："We have pegged our next $1{{nbsp}}billion loan guarantee, first and foremost, to having a rebooting of the reform coalition so that we know who we are working with, but secondarily, to ensuring that the prosecutor general's office gets cleaned up."{{cite web |title=Ukrainian Reforms Two Years After the Maidan Revolution and the Russian Invasion |work=senate.gov |url=https://www.foreign.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/03%2015%2016%20Ukrainian%20Reforms%20Two%20Years%20After%20the%20Maidan%20Revolution%20and%20the%20Russian%20Invasion.pdf |date=2016-03-15 |accessdate=2020-11-08 |archive-date=2019-11-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119210006/https://www.foreign.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/03%2015%2016%20Ukrainian%20Reforms%20Two%20Years%20After%20the%20Maidan%20Revolution%20and%20the%20Russian%20Invasion.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

整个2019年间，拜登在全国民意调查中总体上领先于其他民主党人<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wpsdlocal6.com/news/nbc-wsj-poll-former-vice-president-joe-biden-frontrunner-in/article_24e6b0ee-2256-11ea-9a8d-e79be1ad7f68.html|title=NBC/WSJ poll: Former Vice-President Joe Biden frontrunner in race for Democratic nomination|date=2019-12-19|work=NBC News|accessdate=2020-02-10|archive-date=2020-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213155327/https://www.wpsdlocal6.com/news/nbc-wsj-poll-former-vice-president-joe-biden-frontrunner-in/article_24e6b0ee-2256-11ea-9a8d-e79be1ad7f68.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/biden-is-the-front-runner-but-there-is-no-clear-favorite/|title=Biden Is The Front-Runner, But There's No Clear Favorite|last=Silver|first=Nate|date=2020-01-10|work=FiveThirtyEight|accessdate=2020-02-10|archive-date=2020-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214220639/https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/biden-is-the-front-runner-but-there-is-no-clear-favorite/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。尽管如此，他在{{link-en|2020年民主党爱荷华州初选|2020 Iowa Democratic presidential caucuses|爱荷华州初选}}中得票第四，并在八天后的{{link-en|2020年民主党新罕布什尔州初选|2020 New Hampshire Democratic presidential primary|新罕布什尔州初选}}中列第五<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=2020 Iowa Democratic Caucuses Live Results|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/election-results/iowa/|last=|first=|date=2020-02-03|website=Washington Post|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207234356/https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/election-results/iowa/|archive-date=2020-12-07|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|date=2020-02-11|title=New Hampshire results|work=NBC News|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-primary-elections/new-hampshire-results|dead-url=no|accessdate=2020-02-12|archive-date=2020-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212082135/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-primary-elections/new-hampshire-results}}</ref>。他在{{link-en|2020年民主党内华达州初选|2020 Nevada Democratic presidential caucuses|内华达州党会}}中表现稍好，拿下了获得代表所需的15%选票，但仍落后[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]21.6个百分点<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Nevada Caucus Results|url=https://www.politico.com/2020-election/results/nevada/|last=|first=|date=|website=Politico|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201115105350/https://www.politico.com/2020-election/results/nevada/|archive-date=2020-11-15|access-date=}}</ref>。藉在竞选活动与南卡罗来纳州辩论中对黑人选民发出的强烈呼吁，拜登在{{link-en|2020年南卡罗来纳州民主党初选|2020 South Carolina Democratic presidential primary|南卡罗来纳州的初选}}中以超28点的优势胜出<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/b9872b58b495fd17044f359338ab3f2a|title=Biden wins South Carolina, aims for Super Tuesday momentum|last=|first=|date=2020-02-29|work=Associated Press|accessdate=2020-03-01|archive-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229231101/https://apnews.com/b9872b58b495fd17044f359338ab3f2a|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[彼特·布塔朱吉|彼特·布塔朱吉]]和[[艾米·克罗布彻|艾米·克罗布彻]]相继退选并背书后，他在2020年3月3日的[[超级星期二|超级星期二]]初选中表现卓异，并赢下26场竞争中的18场，包括阿拉巴马州、阿肯色州、缅因州、马萨诸塞州、明尼苏达州、北卡罗来纳州、俄克拉荷马州、田纳西州、德克萨斯州、弗吉尼亚州，从而整体处于领先<ref>{{cite web |last1=Montanaro |first1=Domenico |title=5 Takeaways From Super Tuesday And Joe Biden's Big Night |url=https://www.npr.org/2020/03/04/811868704/5-takeaways-from-super-tuesday-and-joe-bidens-big-night |publisher=NPR |accessdate=2020-11-08 |archive-date=2020-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113205101/https://www.npr.org/2020/03/04/811868704/5-takeaways-from-super-tuesday-and-joe-bidens-big-night |dead-url=no }}</ref>。迈克·布隆伯格和伊丽莎白·沃伦分別在3月4日和5日相繼退选，拜登又在3月10日的四州中扩大了其对桑德斯的优势（爱达荷州、密歇根州、密西西比州、密苏里州）<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/11/politics/2020-primary-election-takeaways/index.html|title=5 takeaways as Biden takes command of Democratic race on Super Tuesday II|date=2020-03-11|work=CNN|accessdate=2020-03-11|archive-date=2020-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311093752/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/11/politics/2020-primary-election-takeaways/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而在3月，拜登一名前女職員塔拉·里德宣稱拜登於1993年曾經「把手伸到她的襯衫和裙子裏」，當時她29歲。拜登的競選團隊否認里德的指控。<ref name="bbc20200430">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world-52468005 |title=美国大选：前助理对拜登的性骚扰指控是怎么回事 |publisher=BBC |date=2020-04-30 |accessdate=2020-04-30 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083436/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world-52468005 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在桑德斯于2020年4月8日中止竞选后，拜登便成为了民主党的推定总统候选人<ref name="NYT4-8-2020">{{Cite news|last=Ember|first=Sydney|date=2020-04-08|title=Bernie Sanders Drops Out of 2020 Democratic Race for President|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/politics/bernie-sanders-drops-out.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2020-04-08|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408160232/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/politics/bernie-sanders-drops-out.html}}</ref>。4月13日，在从各自家里举行的实时直播讨论中，桑德斯背书了拜登<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/13/us/politics/bernie-sanders-joe-biden-endorsement.html|title=Bernie Sanders Endorses Joe Biden for President|last1=Ember|first1=Sydney|last2=Glueck|first2=Katie|date=2020-04-13|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2020-04-13|archive-date=2020-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413182004/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/13/us/politics/bernie-sanders-joe-biden-endorsement.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。前任总统[[奥巴马|奥巴马]]次日背书拜登<ref>{{Cite news |last=Merica |first=Dan |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/14/politics/obama-endorses-biden/index.html |title=Obama endorses Biden for president in video message |date=2020-04-14 |work=CNN |access-date=2020-04-14 |dead-url=no |archive-date=2020-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414183659/https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/14/politics/obama-endorses-biden/index.html }}</ref>。2020年3月间，拜登承诺会将一名女性选作竞选伙伴<ref>{{cite news|title=Joe Biden commits to picking a woman as his running mate|work=Axios|url=https://www.axios.com/joe-biden-woman-running-mate-6add0a5b-2600-43b0-8e83-b38d74042881.html|date=2020-03-16|accessdate=2020-05-03|archive-date=2020-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201008164423/https://www.axios.com/joe-biden-woman-running-mate-6add0a5b-2600-43b0-8e83-b38d74042881.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。6月，拜登拿下了本党总统候选人提名所需的1991名代表数。8月11日，他宣布将[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]参议员[[贺锦丽|贺锦丽]]选定为其竞选搭档，后者亦成为美国史上首个主要党派的[[非裔美国人|非裔]]及[[印度裔美國人|南亚裔]]副总统提名者<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-53739323 |title=Biden VP pick: Kamala Harris chosen as running mate |website=BBC News |date=2020-08-11 |accessdate=2020-08-11 |archive-date=2020-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010223842/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-53739323 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2020年8月18日，拜登正式于{{link-en|2020年民主党全国代表大会|2020 Democratic National Convention}}获提名为[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]][[2020年美國總統選舉|2020年大选]]的总统候选人<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=DNC Nominates Joe Biden to Lead Nation Through Pandemic |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-to-nominate-joe-biden-bill-clinton-alexandria-ocasio-cortez-to-speak-11597777946 |work=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]] |location= |date=2020-08-18 |access-date=2020-08-19 |archive-date=2020-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818221830/https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-to-nominate-joe-biden-bill-clinton-alexandria-ocasio-cortez-to-speak-11597777946 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Joe Biden officially becomes the Democratic Party's nominee on convention's second night |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/2020/08/18/democratic-national-convention-live-updates/ |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |location= |date=2020-08-19 |access-date=2020-08-19 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083542/https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/2020/08/18/democratic-national-convention-live-updates/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schultz |first=Marisa |date=2020-08-18 |title=Democrats formally nominate Joe Biden for president in virtual roll call |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/democrats-formally-nominate-joe-biden-to-be-2020-presidential-nominee |work=[[Fox_News|Fox News]] |location= |access-date=2020-08-19 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115190502/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/democrats-formally-nominate-joe-biden-to-be-2020-presidential-nominee |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

