-president-biden-bipartisan-debt-talks|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Competing Visions: President Obama, Rep. Paul Ryan, Sen. Patty Murray, and House Progressives Release Budget Proposals for 2014|url=https://www.nationalpriorities.org/analysis/2013/budget-proposals-2014/|accessdate=2013-06-03|date=2013-04-10|publisher=National Priorities Project|last1=Hellman|first1=Chris|last2=Kramer|first2=Mattea|archive-date=2013-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131125214704/http://nationalpriorities.org/en/analysis/2013/budget-proposals-2014/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他曾提议扭转部分[[2017年减税与就业法案|2017年减税与就业法案]]中包括的企业减税政策，称这样做不会损害企业的雇佣能力。<ref>{{cite news|date=2020-09-11|title=Joe Biden pledges to roll back Trump's corporate tax cuts on 'day one,' saying it won't hurt businesses' ability to hire|work=Business Insider|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/joe-biden-trumps-tax-cuts-day-one-presidency-economy-2020-9|accessdate=2020-11-13|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122232506/https://www.businessinsider.com/joe-biden-trumps-tax-cuts-day-one-presidency-economy-2020-9|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="#2">{{cite news|date=2020-06-30|title=Biden pledges to roll back Trump's tax cuts: 'A lot of you may not like that'|work=Fox Business|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/money/biden-pledges-to-undo-trumps-tax-cuts-a-lot-of-you-may-not-like-that|accessdate=2020-11-13|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112205316/https://www.foxbusiness.com/money/biden-pledges-to-undo-trumps-tax-cuts-a-lot-of-you-may-not-like-that|dead-url=no}}</ref>他给[[北美自由贸易协议|北美自由贸易协议]]（NAFTA）<ref>{{cite news|title=Final Senate Vote on NAFTA|publisher=Public Citizen|url=http://www.citizen.org/print_article.cfm?ID=15960|accessdate=2008-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080608182639/http://www.citizen.org/print_article.cfm?ID=15960|archive-date=2008-06-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>和[[跨太平洋伙伴关系协定|跨太平洋伙伴关系协定]]投了赞成票。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Biden coaxes Dems on Obama trade deal|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/house/267420-biden-coaxes-dems-on-obama-trade-deal|author=Mike Lillis|date=2016-01-28|website=The Hill|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2019-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107075246/https://thehill.com/homenews/house/267420-biden-coaxes-dems-on-obama-trade-deal|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登是[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|患者保护与平价医疗法案]]（ACA）的坚定支持者。<ref name="ACA203">Dan Diamond, [https://www.politico.com/story/2019/07/15/joe-biden-health-care-plan-1415850 Biden unveils health care plan: Affordable Care Act 2.0] {{Wayback|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/07/15/joe-biden-health-care-plan-1415850 |date=20210103083823 }}, ''Politico'' (July 15, 2019).</ref><ref>Bill Barrow, [https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/biden-aggressively-defends-the-affordable-care-act Biden aggressively defends the Affordable Care Act] {{Wayback|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/biden-aggressively-defends-the-affordable-care-act |date=20210103083902 }}, Associated Press (July 15, 2019).</ref>他推还动了一项在此基础上扩大并发展所覆盖范围的计划，预计将由取消特朗普政府所做的一些减税条款来支付。<ref name="ACA203" />拜登的计划是建立一个公共的[[醫療保險|醫療保險]]体系，目的是将医疗保险的覆盖面扩大到97%的美国人。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Scott|first=Dylan|date=2020-08-20|title=Joe Biden has a chance to finish the work of Obamacare|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2020/8/20/21372511/joe-biden-obamacare-health-care-plan|access-date=2020-11-27|work=[Vox|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105044015/https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2020/8/20/21372511/joe-biden-obamacare-health-care-plan|dead-url=no}}</ref>

拜登支持[[生育权|生育权]]<ref name="RCP2">{{cite web|title=Biden's Pro-Abortion Stance Will Cost Him Moderate Voters|url=https://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2020/03/19/bidens_pro-abortion_stance_will_cost_him_moderate_voters_142701.html|accessdate=2020-04-19|date=2020-03-19|last=Dannenfelser|first=Marjorie|publisher=RealClearPolitics|archive-date=2020-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320144639/https://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2020/03/19/bidens_pro-abortion_stance_will_cost_him_moderate_voters_142701.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Biden|first=Joe|date=2013-05-06|title=May 6: Joe Biden, Kelly Ayotte, Diane Swonk, Tom Brokaw, Chuck Todd|work=[[NBC_News|NBC News]]|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/47311900/ns/meet_the_press-transcripts/t/may-joe-biden-kelly-ayotte-diane-swonk-tom-brokaw-chuck-todd/|accessdate=2013-04-05|archive-date=2013-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130405045344/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/47311900/ns/meet_the_press-transcripts/t/may-joe-biden-kelly-ayotte-diane-swonk-tom-brokaw-chuck-todd/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[羅訴韋德案|羅訴韋德案]]的判决。自2019年以来，他还支持废除{{Link-en|海德修正案|Hyde Amendment}}。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lerer|first=Lisa|date=2019-03-29|title=When Joe Biden Voted to Let States Overturn Roe v. Wade|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/29/us/politics/biden-abortion-rights.html|access-date=2020-08-08|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806121254/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/29/us/politics/biden-abortion-rights.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Biden calls for enshrining Roe v. Wade in federal law|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/22/biden-roe-v-wade-2020-1376712|accessdate=2020-04-19|date=2019-06-22|last=Siders|first=Dave|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|archive-date=2020-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402175549/https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/22/biden-roe-v-wade-2020-1376712|dead-url=no}}</ref>他反对在{{Link-en|极地国家野生动物保护区|Arctic National Wildlife Refuge}}钻探石油，支持政府出资寻找新能源。<ref>{{cite web|title=Presidential Candidates views on ANWR, The Democrats|url=http://www.anwr.org/Politics/Presidential-Candidates-views-on-ANWR-The-Democrats.php|accessdate=2008-08-25|publisher=Arctic Power|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080807162357/http://www.anwr.org/Politics/Presidential-Candidates-views-on-ANWR-The-Democrats.php|archive-date=2008-08-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>他认为美国必须对[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]采取行动。他是参议院最严格的气候相关法案《2007年全球变暖减少污染法案》的共同提案人，此一法案呼吁美国参加联合国气候谈判。<ref>{{cite news|date=2008-01-03|title=A look at the environmental record of Joe Biden, Barack Obama's running mate|magazine=[Grist|url=https://grist.org/article/biden_factsheet/|accessdate=2008-05-04|archive-date=2010-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100526083021/http://www.grist.org/article/biden_factsheet/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他希望在2035年实现美国电力部门无碳化，并在2050年实现零排放。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Carr|first1=Bob|date=2020-09-02|title=Joe Biden's bold climate policies would leave Australia behind|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/sep/02/joe-bidens-bold-climate-policies-would-leave-australia-behind|accessdate=2020-09-21|archive-date=2020-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921170525/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/sep/02/joe-bidens-bold-climate-policies-would-leave-australia-behind|dead-url=no}}</ref>他的方案包括重新加入巴黎协定、[[保育倫理|自然保育]]和建设[[綠色建築|綠色建築]]。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Moore|first1=Elena|date=2020-10-16|title=Trump's And Biden's Plans For The Environment|agency=NPR|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/10/16/920484187/trumps-and-biden-s-plans-for-the-environment|accessdate=2020-10-21|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030113807/https://www.npr.org/2020/10/16/920484187/trumps-and-biden-s-plans-for-the-environment|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登希望向中国和其他国家施压，以减少[[温室气体|温室气体]]排放，必要时可征收[[碳税|碳关税]]。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bade|first1=Gavin|date=2020-10-14|title=How Biden would use trade agreements to fight global warming|work=Politico|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/10/14/biden-trade-fight-global-warming-429495|accessdate=2020-10-22|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021021812/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/10/14/biden-trade-fight-global-warming-429495|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=2020-09-08|title=Biden's hands may be tied on Trump's China tariffs, trade experts say|publisher=CNBC|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/09/08/bidens-hands-may-be-tied-on-trumps-china-tariffs-trade-experts-say-.html|accessdate=2020-10-22|archive-date=2020-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026034203/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/09/08/bidens-hands-may-be-tied-on-trumps-china-tariffs-trade-experts-say-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>作为参议员，他与警察团体建立了深厚的联系。拜登是《{{Link-en|警察权利法案|Law Enforcement Officers' Bill of Rights}}》的主要支持者——此一法案雖受到警察工会支持，但卻為警察局长们反对。作为副总统，他曾担任白宫与警察的联络人。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kranish|first=Michael|date=2020-06-09|title=Joe Biden let police groups write his crime bill. Now, his agenda has changed.|work=The Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/joe-biden-let-police-groups-write-his-crime-bill-now-his-agenda-has-changed/2020/06/08/82ab969e-a434-11ea-8681-7d471bf20207_story.html|accessdate=2020-11-13|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112174038/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/joe-biden-let-police-groups-write-his-crime-bill-now-his-agenda-has-changed/2020/06/08/82ab969e-a434-11ea-8681-7d471bf20207_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Biden repeatedly pushed bill in Senate that critics said would have made investigating police officers for misconduct more difficult|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/10/politics/biden-senate-police-officers-kfile/index.html|accessdate=2020-11-13|date=2020-06-10|publisher=CNN|last1=McDermott|first1=Nathan|last2=Steck|first2=Em|archive-date=2020-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116122904/https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/10/politics/biden-senate-police-officers-kfile/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 外交政策 ===
拜登称，他反对以軍事力量幫助別國實行[[政权更替|政权更迭]]，但支持为反对派运动提供非军事支持。<ref name="NYTForeignPolicy2">[https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/us/politics/joe-biden-foreign-policy.html Foreign Policy, Joseph R. Biden Jr.] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/us/politics/joe-biden-foreign-policy.html |date=20210107123211 }}, ''New York Times'' (2000).</ref>他反对美国[[2011年多国武装干涉利比亚|直接干预利比亚]]<ref>Peter Baker, [https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/10/us/politics/a-biden-run-would-expose-foreign-policy-differences-with-hillary-clinton.html A Biden Run Would Expose Foreign Policy Differences With Hillary Clinton] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/10/us/politics/a-biden-run-would-expose-foreign-policy-differences-with-hillary-clinton.html |date=20201216223923 }}, ''New York Times'' (October 10, 2015): "She argued for the military intervention that ultimately toppled Muammar el-Qaddaf in Libya while he opposed it."</ref><ref name="OddCouple2">[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/28/us/politics/barack-obama-biden.html Biden and Obama's 'Odd Couple' Relationship Aged Into Family Ties] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/28/us/politics/barack-obama-biden.html |date=20200606093422 }}, ''New York Times'' (April 28, 2019): "He was also the in-house skeptic on the use of force, arguing against a troop surge to Afghanistan, military intervention in Libya and the raid that killed Osama bin Laden."</ref>，但支持北约主导对[[利比亚|利比亚]]的军事干预。<ref>{{cite web|last=Memoli|first=Michael A.|date=2011-10-20|title=Kadafi death: Joe Biden says 'NATO got it right' in Libya|url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-xpm-2011-oct-20-la-pn-santorum-kadafi-20111020-story.html|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=2020-12-25|archive-date=2020-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214025400/https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-xpm-2011-oct-20-la-pn-santorum-kadafi-20111020-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他曾投票反对美国参与[[海湾战争|海湾战争]]，<ref>{{cite news|last=Wehner|first=Peter|title=Biden Was Wrong On the Cold War|work=The Wall Street Journal|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB122049148440397625|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081006022121/http://online.wsj.com/public/article_print/SB122049148440397625.html|archive-date=2008-10-06|accessdate=2020-12-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>投票支持美国参与[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]。<ref name="FarleyRecord2">{{cite news|author=Robert Farley|date=2019-09-10|title=Biden's Record on Iraq War|work=FactCheck.org|publisher=Annenberg Public Policy Center|url=https://www.factcheck.org/2019/09/bidens-record-on-iraq-war/|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107172331/https://www.factcheck.org/2019/09/bidens-record-on-iraq-war/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他还支持[[以巴冲突|以巴冲突]]的[[兩國方案|兩國方案]]。<ref name="JTA20192">[https://www.jta.org/2019/12/12/united-states/where-does-joe-biden-stand-on-anti-semitism-israel-and-other-issues-that-matter-to-jewish-voters-in-2020 Where does Joe Biden stand on anti-Semitism, Israel and other issues that matter to Jewish voters in 2020?] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jta.org/2019/12/12/united-states/where-does-joe-biden-stand-on-anti-semitism-israel-and-other-issues-that-matter-to-jewish-voters-in-2020 |date=20210111070241 }}, Jewish Telegraphic Agency (December 12, 2019).</ref>拜登承诺结束美国对[[沙特领导的干预也门行动|沙特领导的干预也门行动]]的支持，并重新评估与[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]的关系。<ref name="foreign-policy2">{{cite news|title=The Democratic candidates on foreign policy|work=[[Foreign_Policy|Foreign Policy]]|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020-election/|accessdate=2020-12-14|archive-date=2020-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200616084737/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020-election/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他称[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝鲜]]是一只“[[纸老虎|纸老虎]]”。<ref name="CFR2">{{cite web|title=Joseph R. Biden, Jr. – Council on Foreign Relations|url=http://www.cfr.org/bios/1451/joseph_r_biden_jr.html|accessdate=2008-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080206202245/http://www.cfr.org/bios/1451/joseph_r_biden_jr.html|archive-date=2008-02-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>作为副总统，拜登支持奥巴马的[[古巴解凍|古巴解凍]]政策。<ref name="Engage2">[https://www.engagecuba.org/2020-presidential-election 2020 presidential election] {{Wayback|url=https://www.engagecuba.org/2020-presidential-election |date=20210103084023 }}, Engage Cuba Coalition (last accessed May 1, 2020).</ref>他曾表示，作为总统，他将恢复美国在联合国主要机构的成员资格，如[[联合国教育、科学及文化组织|联合国教育、科学及文化组织]]（UNESCO）和[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]（WHO）<ref>{{Cite web|title=The US formally announced its withdrawal from the World Health Organization|url=https://www.livescience.com/trump-exits-who-united-states.html|last=July 2020|first=Rafi Letzter-Staff Writer 07|language=en|access-date=2020-11-20|website=livescience.com|archive-date=2020-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118203522/https://www.livescience.com/trump-exits-who-united-states.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并可能加入[[联合国人权理事会|联合国人权理事会]]。<ref name="LeeWeissert2">Matthew Lee & Weissert, [https://apnews.com/1d2a57631fee12c761f91053124606ab Biden eyes major foreign policy shifts if he wins] {{Wayback|url=https://apnews.com/1d2a57631fee12c761f91053124606ab |date=20210107211459 }}, Associated Press (August 1, 2020).</ref>

==== 中华人民共和国 ====
{{See also|中美關係}}
[[File:Vice_President_Biden_Delivers_Remarks_at_the_Joint_Opening_Session.jpg|upright=1.2]]举行的[[中美战略与经济对话|中美战略与经济对话]]上发言]]

拜登认为美国对中国的政策应是与之共事（Engagement）及融合（Integrate）中国到国际秩序中。他同时强调必须推动中国遵循法律和政治方面的国际准则，以及巩固现有联盟以提防中国异常地侵犯美国及其盟国的根本利益。他反对把中国视为敌人，也不以中国为盟友，而是认识到中美之间既有竞争也有共同利益。他认为能源及环境是对中关系的两个特别重要的领域。<ref name="BidenLetter">Joseph R. Biden, Jr., Opening statement at the Senate hearing titled -{“U.S. - China Relations in the Era of Globalization.”}-[http://biden.senate.gov/press/press_releases/release/?id=143f5fd3-1cae-46ac-8675-6267f081377f  "Senate Press Release"] {{Wayback|url=http://biden.senate.gov/press/press_releases/release/?id=143f5fd3-1cae-46ac-8675-6267f081377f |date=20080829011311 }}, 2008-5-15, 查阅于2008-8-23</ref>作为联邦参议院外交委员会主席，他于2007年要求议会研究服务（Congressional Research Service）全面研究中国在亚非拉正在增长的软势力，<ref name="US_China_Report">Congressional Research Service, Library of Congress, [http://biden.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/CRSChinaReport.pdf "China's Foriegn Policy and "Soft Power" in South America, Asia, and Africa"] {{Wayback|url=http://biden.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/CRSChinaReport.pdf |date=20080829013032 }} 2008-4, 查阅于2008-8-23</ref>并于次年主持了参议院“全球化时代的美中关系”听证会，<ref name="BidenLetter"/>对中国的国情及外交有较一般美国政治家更广泛，深入的认识及思考。

拜登支持[[一个中国|一个中国]]政策，主張結束自2018年爆發的[[中美贸易战|中美贸易战]]并終止川普政府對中國貨品加徵的[[特朗普关税|額外關稅]]。<ref name="CNARUCN" />比起川普政府，拜登更加願意增進和中國的合作關係。因為拜登認為中國是美國的競爭對手兼合作伙伴而非敵國。<ref name="CNARUCN">{{Cite web |title=拜登：美國最大威脅是俄羅斯 中國是最大競爭者 |url=https://project.cna.com.tw/20201005-USelection/202010260310 |accessdate=2020-11-05 |date=2020-10-27 |publisher=中央社 |language=zh-tw |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084052/https://project.cna.com.tw/20201005-USelection/202010260310 |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登曾于2011年9月7日在《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》發表題為《中國崛起不是我們的終結》（China's Rise Isn't Our Demise）的文章。称虽然中国崛起带来挑战，但“美国和中国合作的同时也在竞争。”拜登相信，“美国能够并将在这种竞争中蓬勃发展。”拜登称美国的政治和经济制度在竞争中有利。而如果中国想要向创新型经济转型，则必须改变制度。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/08/opinion/chinas-rise-isnt-our-demise.html |script-title=en:China’s Rise Isn’t Our Demise |author=JOSEPH R. BIDEN Jr. |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2011-09-07 |accessdate=2020-09-08 |archive-date=2021-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128005019/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/08/opinion/chinas-rise-isnt-our-demise.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年起拜登關於中國的言論變得比往年更加尖銳，曾經公開批評[[中國共產黨中央委員會總書記|中共中央總書記]][[習近平|習近平]]為「惡棍」，並指控时任總統[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]巴結習近平。<ref>{{cite news |title=In Biden, China Sees an ‘Old Friend’ and Possible Foe |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/22/world/asia/biden-china-election-trump.html |publisher=The New York Times |date=2020-09-22 |accessdate=2020-11-06 |archive-date=2021-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205064209/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/22/world/asia/biden-china-election-trump.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=美國總統大選辯論，川普和拜登如何談論中國？ |url=https://cn.nytimes.com/usa/20201023/us-election-debate-china/zh-hant/ |publisher=紐約時報中文網 |author=MARK LANDLER |date=2020-10-23 |accessdate=2020-11-06 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103084103/https://cn.nytimes.com/usa/20201023/us-election-debate-china/zh-hant/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Joe Biden’s Record on China and Taiwan |url=https://thediplomat.com/2020/03/joe-bidens-record-on-china-and-taiwan/ |publisher=The Diplomat |date=2020-03-06 |accessdate=2020-11-06 |archive-date=2021-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127042251/https://thediplomat.com/2020/03/joe-bidens-record-on-china-and-taiwan/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登亦抨擊中國[[新疆再教育營|新疆再教育營]]的人權問題，並且表示當選總統後將會延續川普的反中政策來反制中國「濫用經濟政策」的手段。<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|date=2020-09-11|title=Joe Biden pledges to roll back Trump's corporate tax cuts on 'day one,' saying it won't hurt businesses' ability to hire|work=Business Insider|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/joe-biden-trumps-tax-cuts-day-one-presidency-economy-2020-9|accessdate=2020-11-13|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122232506/https://www.businessinsider.com/joe-biden-trumps-tax-cuts-day-one-presidency-economy-2020-9|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="#2"/>拜登表示，美国需要对中国"强硬起来"，建立"美国盟友和伙伴的统一战线，以对抗中国的虐待行为和侵犯人权行为。"<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Why America Must Lead Again|url=https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/united-states/2020-01-23/why-america-must-lead-again|last=Biden|first=Joseph R.|last2=Jr|date=2020-11-30|language=en-US|issn=0015-7120|journal=|access-date=2021-03-23|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129012323/https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/united-states/2020-01-23/why-america-must-lead-again|dead-url=no}}</ref>拜登承诺，如果当选，他将对进行压迫的中国政府官员和实体进行[[經濟制裁|經濟制裁]]和商业限制。<ref name="WongCrowleySwanson2">{{cite news|last1=Edward|first1=Wong|last2=Crawley|first2=Michael|last3=Swanson|first3=Ana|date=2020-09-06|title=Joe Biden's China Journey|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/06/us/politics/biden-china.html|accessdate=2020-11-13|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112163033/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/06/us/politics/biden-china.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年12月，他宣布会继续保持對華關稅，將與盟友共同制衡[[中华人民共和国|中國]]。<ref>{{Cite web |title=拜登：不會取消針對華關稅，將與盟友共同制衡中國 |url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese-news-55184463 |accessdate=2020-12-04 |date=2020-12-04 |publisher=BBC中文網 |language=zh-hant |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121070644/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese-news-55184463 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2021年2月，拜登称中国是对美国"繁荣、安全和民主价值"构成挑战的"最严重的竞争对手"。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Remarks by President Biden on America's Place in the World|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/02/04/remarks-by-president-biden-on-americas-place-in-the-world/|accessdate=2021-03-23|date=2021-02-05|work=The White House|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215153831/https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/02/04/remarks-by-president-biden-on-americas-place-in-the-world/|dead-url=no}}</ref>隨後拜登在当选总统后首次与习近平通话时表达了对中国在新疆"胁迫和不公平"的经济行为和侵犯人权行为的担忧。<ref>{{Cite web|title=President Biden Raises Human Rights and Trade Concerns in First Call With China's Xi|url=https://time.com/5938307/biden-xi-china-first-call/|accessdate=2021-03-23|work=Time|archive-date=2021-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216041626/https://time.com/5938307/biden-xi-china-first-call/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2021年4月28日，拜登在上任美國總統100天前夕，到國會發表約65分鐘的演講，其間多次提及[[中国威胁论|中國的威脅]]，他稱[[習近平|習近平]]等[[獨裁者|獨裁者]]認為在21世紀[[民主制度|民主制度]]不敵[[專制主義|專制主義]]，拜登表明會維護美國利益，應對中國的挑戰。拜登在演說中強調專制不會贏得未來，未來屬於美國<ref>{{Cite web|title=拜登：習近平在打賭美國的民主趕不上專制|url=https://www.voacantonese.com/a/Biden-autocracy-democracy-20210428/5871145.html|work=美國之音|date=2021-04-29|access-date=2021-04-29|archive-date=2021-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501045747/https://www.voacantonese.com/a/Biden-autocracy-democracy-20210428/5871145.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=首國會演說　倡世代投資先於貿戰　拜登籲投32萬億與華競爭|url=https://hk.appledaily.com/international/20210430/OWYJ7T3MBFAP5BGPSWF2DFYVGU/|work=蘋果日報|date=2021-04-30|access-date=2021-04-30|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505105309/https://hk.appledaily.com/international/20210430/OWYJ7T3MBFAP5BGPSWF2DFYVGU/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

